var book = {
	"name": "1 Kings",
	"numChapters": 22,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>When King David was very old, he could not keep warm even when they put covers over him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So his attendants said to him, “Let us look for a young virgin to serve the king and take care of him. She can lie beside him so that our lord the king may keep warm.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then they searched throughout Israel for a beautiful young woman and found Abishag,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8721A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8721A\"></sup> a Shunammite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8721B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8721B\"></sup> and brought her to the king.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The woman was very beautiful; she took care of the king and waited on him, but the king had no sexual relations with her.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now Adonijah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8723C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8723C\"></sup> whose mother was Haggith, put himself forward and said, “I will be king.” So he got chariots<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8723D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8723D\"></sup> and horses ready, with fifty men to run ahead of him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>(His father had never rebuked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8724E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8724E\"></sup> him by asking, “Why do you behave as you do?” He was also very handsome and was born next after Absalom.)",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Adonijah conferred with Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8725F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8725F\"></sup> son of Zeruiah and with Abiathar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8725G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8725G\"></sup> the priest, and they gave him their support.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But Zadok<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8726H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8726H\"></sup> the priest, Benaiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8726I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8726I\"></sup> son of Jehoiada, Nathan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8726J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8726J\"></sup> the prophet, Shimei<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8726K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8726K\"></sup> and Rei and David’s special guard<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8726L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8726L\"></sup> did not join Adonijah.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Adonijah then sacrificed sheep, cattle and fattened calves at the Stone of Zoheleth near En Rogel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8727M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8727M\"></sup> He invited all his brothers, the king’s sons,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8727N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8727N\"></sup> and all the royal officials of Judah,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>but he did not invite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8728O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8728O\"></sup> Nathan the prophet or Benaiah or the special guard or his brother Solomon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8728P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8728P\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Nathan asked Bathsheba,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8729Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8729Q\"></sup> Solomon’s mother, “Have you not heard that Adonijah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8729R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8729R\"></sup> the son of Haggith, has become king, and our lord David knows nothing about it?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now then, let me advise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8730S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8730S\"></sup> you how you can save your own life and the life of your son Solomon.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Go in to King David and say to him, ‘My lord the king, did you not swear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8731T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8731T\"></sup> to me your servant: “Surely Solomon your son shall be king after me, and he will sit on my throne”? Why then has Adonijah become king?’",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>While you are still there talking to the king, I will come in and add my word to what you have said.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So Bathsheba went to see the aged king in his room, where Abishag<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8733U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8733U\"></sup> the Shunammite was attending him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Bathsheba bowed down, prostrating herself before the king.“What is it you want?” the king asked.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>She said to him, “My lord, you yourself swore<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8735V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8735V\"></sup> to me your servant by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God: ‘Solomon your son shall be king after me, and he will sit on my throne.’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But now Adonijah has become king, and you, my lord the king, do not know about it.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He has sacrificed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8737W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8737W\"></sup> great numbers of cattle, fattened calves, and sheep, and has invited all the king’s sons, Abiathar the priest and Joab the commander of the army, but he has not invited Solomon your servant.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>My lord the king, the eyes of all Israel are on you, to learn from you who will sit on the throne of my lord the king after him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Otherwise, as soon as my lord the king is laid to rest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8739X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8739X\"></sup> with his ancestors, I and my son Solomon will be treated as criminals.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>While she was still speaking with the king, Nathan the prophet arrived.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And the king was told, “Nathan the prophet is here.” So he went before the king and bowed with his face to the ground.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Nathan said, “Have you, my lord the king, declared that Adonijah shall be king after you, and that he will sit on your throne?",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Today he has gone down and sacrificed great numbers of cattle, fattened calves, and sheep. He has invited all the king’s sons, the commanders of the army and Abiathar the priest. Right now they are eating and drinking with him and saying, ‘Long live King Adonijah!’",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But me your servant, and Zadok the priest, and Benaiah son of Jehoiada, and your servant Solomon he did not invite.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8744Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8744Y\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Is this something my lord the king has done without letting his servants know who should sit on the throne of my lord the king after him?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then King David said, “Call in Bathsheba.” So she came into the king’s presence and stood before him.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The king then took an oath: “As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, who has delivered me out of every trouble,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8747AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8747AA\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>I will surely carry out this very day what I swore<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8748AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8748AB\"></sup> to you by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel: Solomon your son shall be king after me, and he will sit on my throne in my place.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then Bathsheba bowed down with her face to the ground, prostrating herself before the king, and said, “May my lord King David live forever!”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>King David said, “Call in Zadok<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8750AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8750AC\"></sup> the priest, Nathan the prophet and Benaiah son of Jehoiada.” When they came before the king,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>he said to them: “Take your lord’s servants with you and have Solomon my son mount my own mule<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8751AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8751AD\"></sup> and take him down to Gihon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8751AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8751AE\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>There have Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet anoint<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8752AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8752AF\"></sup> him king over Israel. Blow the trumpet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8752AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8752AG\"></sup> and shout, ‘Long live King Solomon!’",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then you are to go up with him, and he is to come and sit on my throne and reign in my place. I have appointed him ruler over Israel and Judah.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Benaiah son of Jehoiada answered the king, “Amen! May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of my lord the king, so declare it.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with my lord the king, so may he be with<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8755AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8755AH\"></sup> Solomon to make his throne even greater<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8755AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8755AI\"></sup> than the throne of my lord King David!”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>So Zadok<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8756AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8756AJ\"></sup> the priest, Nathan the prophet, Benaiah son of Jehoiada, the Kerethites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8756AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8756AK\"></sup> and the Pelethites went down and had Solomon mount King David’s mule, and they escorted him to Gihon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8756AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8756AL\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Zadok the priest took the horn of oil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8757AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8757AM\"></sup> from the sacred tent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8757AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8757AN\"></sup> and anointed Solomon. Then they sounded the trumpet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8757AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8757AO\"></sup> and all the people shouted,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8757AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8757AP\"></sup> “Long live King Solomon!”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And all the people went up after him, playing pipes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8758AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8758AQ\"></sup> and rejoicing greatly, so that the ground shook with the sound.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Adonijah and all the guests who were with him heard it as they were finishing their feast. On hearing the sound of the trumpet, Joab asked, “What’s the meaning of all the noise in the city?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8759AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8759AR\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Even as he was speaking, Jonathan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8760AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8760AS\"></sup> son of Abiathar the priest arrived. Adonijah said, “Come in. A worthy man like you must be bringing good news.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8760AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8760AT\"></sup>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>“Not at all!” Jonathan answered. “Our lord King David has made Solomon king.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>The king has sent with him Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet, Benaiah son of Jehoiada, the Kerethites and the Pelethites, and they have put him on the king’s mule,",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>and Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet have anointed him king at Gihon. From there they have gone up cheering, and the city resounds<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8763AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8763AU\"></sup> with it. That’s the noise you hear.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Moreover, Solomon has taken his seat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8764AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8764AV\"></sup> on the royal throne.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Also, the royal officials have come to congratulate our lord King David, saying, ‘May your God make Solomon’s name more famous than yours and his throne greater<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8765AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8765AW\"></sup> than yours!’ And the king bowed in worship on his bed",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>and said, ‘Praise be to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, who has allowed my eyes to see a successor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8766AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8766AX\"></sup> on my throne today.’”",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>At this, all Adonijah’s guests rose in alarm and dispersed.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>But Adonijah, in fear of Solomon, went and took hold of the horns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8768AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8768AY\"></sup> of the altar.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Then Solomon was told, “Adonijah is afraid of King Solomon and is clinging to the horns of the altar. He says, ‘Let King Solomon swear to me today that he will not put his servant to death with the sword.’”",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Solomon replied, “If he shows himself to be worthy, not a hair<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8770AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8770AZ\"></sup> of his head will fall to the ground; but if evil is found in him, he will die.”",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>Then King Solomon sent men, and they brought him down from the altar. And Adonijah came and bowed down to King Solomon, and Solomon said, “Go to your home.”"
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>When the time drew near for David to die,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8772B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8772B\"></sup> he gave a charge to Solomon his son.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“I am about to go the way of all the earth,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8773C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8773C\"></sup> he said. “So be strong,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8773D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8773D\"></sup> act like a man,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and observe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8774E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8774E\"></sup> what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God requires: Walk in obedience to him, and keep his decrees and commands, his laws and regulations, as written in the Law of Moses. Do this so that you may prosper<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8774F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8774F\"></sup> in all you do and wherever you go",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> may keep his promise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8775G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8775G\"></sup> to me: ‘If your descendants watch how they live, and if they walk faithfully<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8775H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8775H\"></sup> before me with all their heart and soul, you will never fail to have a successor on the throne of Israel.’",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Now you yourself know what Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8776I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8776I\"></sup> son of Zeruiah did to me—what he did to the two commanders of Israel’s armies, Abner<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8776J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8776J\"></sup> son of Ner and Amasa<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8776K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8776K\"></sup> son of Jether. He killed them, shedding their blood in peacetime as if in battle, and with that blood he stained the belt around his waist and the sandals on his feet.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Deal with him according to your wisdom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8777L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8777L\"></sup> but do not let his gray head go down to the grave in peace.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“But show kindness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8778M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8778M\"></sup> to the sons of Barzillai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8778N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8778N\"></sup> of Gilead and let them be among those who eat at your table.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8778O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8778O\"></sup> They stood by me when I fled from your brother Absalom.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“And remember, you have with you Shimei<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8779P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8779P\"></sup> son of Gera, the Benjamite from Bahurim, who called down bitter curses on me the day I went to Mahanaim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8779Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8779Q\"></sup> When he came down to meet me at the Jordan, I swore<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8779R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8779R\"></sup> to him by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: ‘I will not put you to death by the sword.’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But now, do not consider him innocent. You are a man of wisdom;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8780S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8780S\"></sup> you will know what to do to him. Bring his gray head down to the grave in blood.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then David rested with his ancestors and was buried<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8781T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8781T\"></sup> in the City of David.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8781U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8781U\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He had reigned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8782V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8782V\"></sup> forty years over Israel—seven years in Hebron and thirty-three in Jerusalem.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So Solomon sat on the throne<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8783W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8783W\"></sup> of his father David, and his rule was firmly established.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8783X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8783X\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now Adonijah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8784Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8784Y\"></sup> the son of Haggith, went to Bathsheba, Solomon’s mother. Bathsheba asked him, “Do you come peacefully?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8784Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8784Z\"></sup>He answered, “Yes, peacefully.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then he added, “I have something to say to you.”“You may say it,” she replied.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“As you know,” he said, “the kingdom was mine. All Israel looked to me as their king. But things changed, and the kingdom has gone to my brother; for it has come to him from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now I have one request to make of you. Do not refuse me.”“You may make it,” she said.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So he continued, “Please ask King Solomon—he will not refuse you—to give me Abishag<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8788AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8788AA\"></sup> the Shunammite as my wife.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Very well,” Bathsheba replied, “I will speak to the king for you.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When Bathsheba went to King Solomon to speak to him for Adonijah, the king stood up to meet her, bowed down to her and sat down on his throne. He had a throne brought for the king’s mother,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8790AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8790AB\"></sup> and she sat down at his right hand.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8790AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8790AC\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“I have one small request to make of you,” she said. “Do not refuse me.”The king replied, “Make it, my mother; I will not refuse you.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So she said, “Let Abishag<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8792AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8792AD\"></sup> the Shunammite be given in marriage to your brother Adonijah.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>King Solomon answered his mother, “Why do you request Abishag<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8793AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8793AE\"></sup> the Shunammite for Adonijah? You might as well request the kingdom for him—after all, he is my older brother<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8793AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8793AF\"></sup>—yes, for him and for Abiathar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8793AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8793AG\"></sup> the priest and Joab son of Zeruiah!”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then King Solomon swore by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: “May God deal with me, be it ever so severely,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8794AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8794AH\"></sup> if Adonijah does not pay with his life for this request!",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And now, as surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives—he who has established me securely on the throne of my father David and has founded a dynasty for me as he promised<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8795AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8795AI\"></sup>—Adonijah shall be put to death today!”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So King Solomon gave orders to Benaiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8796AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8796AJ\"></sup> son of Jehoiada, and he struck down Adonijah and he died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8796AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8796AK\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>To Abiathar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8797AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8797AL\"></sup> the priest the king said, “Go back to your fields in Anathoth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8797AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8797AM\"></sup> You deserve to die, but I will not put you to death now, because you carried the ark<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8797AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8797AN\"></sup> of the Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> before my father David and shared all my father’s hardships.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8797AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8797AO\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So Solomon removed Abiathar from the priesthood of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, fulfilling<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8798AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8798AP\"></sup> the word the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had spoken at Shiloh about the house of Eli.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>When the news reached Joab, who had conspired with Adonijah though not with Absalom, he fled to the tent of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and took hold of the horns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8799AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8799AQ\"></sup> of the altar.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>King Solomon was told that Joab had fled to the tent of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and was beside the altar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8800AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8800AR\"></sup> Then Solomon ordered Benaiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8800AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8800AS\"></sup> son of Jehoiada, “Go, strike him down!”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So Benaiah entered the tent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8801AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8801AT\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said to Joab, “The king says, ‘Come out!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8801AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8801AU\"></sup>’”But he answered, “No, I will die here.”Benaiah reported to the king, “This is how Joab answered me.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then the king commanded Benaiah, “Do as he says. Strike him down and bury him, and so clear me and my whole family of the guilt of the innocent blood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8802AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8802AV\"></sup> that Joab shed.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will repay<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8803AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8803AW\"></sup> him for the blood he shed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8803AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8803AX\"></sup> because without my father David knowing it he attacked two men and killed them with the sword. Both of them—Abner son of Ner, commander of Israel’s army, and Amasa<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8803AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8803AY\"></sup> son of Jether, commander of Judah’s army—were better<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8803AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8803AZ\"></sup> men and more upright than he.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>May the guilt of their blood rest on the head of Joab and his descendants forever. But on David and his descendants, his house and his throne, may there be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s peace forever.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>So Benaiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8805BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8805BA\"></sup> son of Jehoiada went up and struck down Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8805BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8805BB\"></sup> and killed him, and he was buried at his home out in the country.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The king put Benaiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8806BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8806BC\"></sup> son of Jehoiada over the army in Joab’s position and replaced Abiathar with Zadok<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8806BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8806BD\"></sup> the priest.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then the king sent for Shimei<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8807BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8807BE\"></sup> and said to him, “Build yourself a house in Jerusalem and live there, but do not go anywhere else.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>The day you leave and cross the Kidron Valley,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8808BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8808BF\"></sup> you can be sure you will die; your blood will be on your own head.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8808BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8808BG\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Shimei answered the king, “What you say is good. Your servant will do as my lord the king has said.” And Shimei stayed in Jerusalem for a long time.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>But three years later, two of Shimei’s slaves ran off to Achish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8810BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8810BH\"></sup> son of Maakah, king of Gath, and Shimei was told, “Your slaves are in Gath.”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>At this, he saddled his donkey and went to Achish at Gath in search of his slaves. So Shimei went away and brought the slaves back from Gath.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>When Solomon was told that Shimei had gone from Jerusalem to Gath and had returned,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>the king summoned Shimei and said to him, “Did I not make you swear by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and warn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8813BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8813BI\"></sup> you, ‘On the day you leave to go anywhere else, you can be sure you will die’? At that time you said to me, ‘What you say is good. I will obey.’",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Why then did you not keep your oath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and obey the command I gave you?”",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>The king also said to Shimei, “You know in your heart all the wrong<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8815BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8815BJ\"></sup> you did to my father David. Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will repay you for your wrongdoing.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>But King Solomon will be blessed, and David’s throne will remain secure<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8816BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8816BK\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> forever.”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Then the king gave the order to Benaiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8817BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8817BL\"></sup> son of Jehoiada, and he went out and struck Shimei<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8817BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8817BM\"></sup> down and he died.The kingdom was now established<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8817BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8817BN\"></sup> in Solomon’s hands."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Solomon made an alliance with Pharaoh king of Egypt and married<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8818B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8818B\"></sup> his daughter.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8818C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8818C\"></sup> He brought her to the City of David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8818D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8818D\"></sup> until he finished building his palace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8818E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8818E\"></sup> and the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the wall around Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The people, however, were still sacrificing at the high places,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8819F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8819F\"></sup> because a temple had not yet been built for the Name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8819G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8819G\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Solomon showed his love<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8820H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8820H\"></sup> for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by walking<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8820I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8820I\"></sup> according to the instructions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8820J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8820J\"></sup> given him by his father David, except that he offered sacrifices and burned incense on the high places.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8820K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8820K\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The king went to Gibeon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8821L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8821L\"></sup> to offer sacrifices, for that was the most important high place, and Solomon offered a thousand burnt offerings on that altar.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>At Gibeon the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8822M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8822M\"></sup> to Solomon during the night in a dream,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8822N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8822N\"></sup> and God said, “Ask<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8822O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8822O\"></sup> for whatever you want me to give you.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Solomon answered, “You have shown great kindness to your servant, my father David, because he was faithful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8823P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8823P\"></sup> to you and righteous and upright in heart. You have continued this great kindness to him and have given him a son<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8823Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8823Q\"></sup> to sit on his throne this very day.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Now, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, you have made your servant king in place of my father David. But I am only a little child<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8824R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8824R\"></sup> and do not know how to carry out my duties.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Your servant is here among the people you have chosen,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8825S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8825S\"></sup> a great people, too numerous to count or number.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8825T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8825T\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So give your servant a discerning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8826U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8826U\"></sup> heart to govern your people and to distinguish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8826V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8826V\"></sup> between right and wrong. For who is able<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8826W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8826W\"></sup> to govern this great people of yours?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The Lord was pleased that Solomon had asked for this.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So God said to him, “Since you have asked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8828X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8828X\"></sup> for this and not for long life or wealth for yourself, nor have asked for the death of your enemies but for discernment<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8828Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8828Y\"></sup> in administering justice,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I will do what you have asked.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8829Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8829Z\"></sup> I will give you a wise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8829AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8829AA\"></sup> and discerning heart, so that there will never have been anyone like you, nor will there ever be.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Moreover, I will give you what you have not<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8830AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8830AB\"></sup> asked for—both wealth and honor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8830AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8830AC\"></sup>—so that in your lifetime you will have no equal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8830AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8830AD\"></sup> among kings.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And if you walk<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8831AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8831AE\"></sup> in obedience to me and keep my decrees and commands as David your father did, I will give you a long life.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8831AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8831AF\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Solomon awoke<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8832AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8832AG\"></sup>—and he realized it had been a dream.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8832AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8832AH\"></sup>He returned to Jerusalem, stood before the ark of the Lord’s covenant and sacrificed burnt offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8832AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8832AI\"></sup> and fellowship offerings.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8832AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8832AJ\"></sup> Then he gave a feast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8832AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8832AK\"></sup> for all his court.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now two prostitutes came to the king and stood before him.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>One of them said, “Pardon me, my lord. This woman and I live in the same house, and I had a baby while she was there with me.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The third day after my child was born, this woman also had a baby. We were alone; there was no one in the house but the two of us.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“During the night this woman’s son died because she lay on him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So she got up in the middle of the night and took my son from my side while I your servant was asleep. She put him by her breast and put her dead son by my breast.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The next morning, I got up to nurse my son—and he was dead! But when I looked at him closely in the morning light, I saw that it wasn’t the son I had borne.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The other woman said, “No! The living one is my son; the dead one is yours.”But the first one insisted, “No! The dead one is yours; the living one is mine.” And so they argued before the king.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The king said, “This one says, ‘My son is alive and your son is dead,’ while that one says, ‘No! Your son is dead and mine is alive.’”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then the king said, “Bring me a sword.” So they brought a sword for the king.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He then gave an order: “Cut the living child in two and give half to one and half to the other.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The woman whose son was alive was deeply moved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8843AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8843AL\"></sup> out of love for her son and said to the king, “Please, my lord, give her the living baby! Don’t kill him!”But the other said, “Neither I nor you shall have him. Cut him in two!”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then the king gave his ruling: “Give the living baby to the first woman. Do not kill him; she is his mother.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>When all Israel heard the verdict the king had given, they held the king in awe, because they saw that he had wisdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8845AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8845AM\"></sup> from God to administer justice."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>So King Solomon ruled over all Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And these were his chief officials:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8847A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8847A\"></sup>Azariah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8847B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8847B\"></sup> son of Zadok—the priest;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Elihoreph and Ahijah, sons of Shisha—secretaries;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8848C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8848C\"></sup>Jehoshaphat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8848D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8848D\"></sup> son of Ahilud—recorder;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Benaiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8849E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8849E\"></sup> son of Jehoiada—commander in chief;Zadok<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8849F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8849F\"></sup> and Abiathar—priests;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Azariah son of Nathan—in charge of the district governors;Zabud son of Nathan—a priest and adviser to the king;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Ahishar—palace administrator;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8851G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8851G\"></sup>Adoniram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8851H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8851H\"></sup> son of Abda—in charge of forced labor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8851I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8851I\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Solomon had twelve district governors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8852J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8852J\"></sup> over all Israel, who supplied provisions for the king and the royal household. Each one had to provide supplies for one month in the year.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>These are their names:Ben-Hur—in the hill country<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8853K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8853K\"></sup> of Ephraim;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Ben-Deker—in Makaz, Shaalbim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8854L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8854L\"></sup> Beth Shemesh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8854M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8854M\"></sup> and Elon Bethhanan;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Ben-Hesed—in Arubboth (Sokoh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8855N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8855N\"></sup> and all the land of Hepher<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8855O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8855O\"></sup> were his);",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Ben-Abinadab—in Naphoth Dor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8856P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8856P\"></sup> (he was married to Taphath daughter of Solomon);",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Baana son of Ahilud—in Taanach and Megiddo, and in all of Beth Shan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8857Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8857Q\"></sup> next to Zarethan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8857R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8857R\"></sup> below Jezreel, from Beth Shan to Abel Meholah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8857S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8857S\"></sup> across to Jokmeam;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8857T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8857T\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Ben-Geber—in Ramoth Gilead (the settlements of Jair<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8858U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8858U\"></sup> son of Manasseh in Gilead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8858V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8858V\"></sup> were his, as well as the region of Argob in Bashan and its sixty large walled cities<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8858W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8858W\"></sup> with bronze gate bars);",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Ahinadab son of Iddo—in Mahanaim;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8859X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8859X\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Ahimaaz<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8860Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8860Y\"></sup>—in Naphtali (he had married Basemath daughter of Solomon);",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Baana son of Hushai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8861Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8861Z\"></sup>—in Asher and in Aloth;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Jehoshaphat son of Paruah—in Issachar;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Shimei<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8863AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8863AA\"></sup> son of Ela—in Benjamin;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Geber son of Uri—in Gilead (the country of Sihon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8864AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8864AB\"></sup> king of the Amorites and the country of Og<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8864AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8864AC\"></sup> king of Bashan). He was the only governor over the district.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The people of Judah and Israel were as numerous as the sand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8865AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8865AD\"></sup> on the seashore; they ate, they drank and they were happy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8865AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8865AE\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And Solomon ruled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8866AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8866AF\"></sup> over all the kingdoms from the Euphrates River<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8866AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8866AG\"></sup> to the land of the Philistines, as far as the border of Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8866AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8866AH\"></sup> These countries brought tribute<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8866AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8866AI\"></sup> and were Solomon’s subjects all his life.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Solomon’s daily provisions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8867AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8867AJ\"></sup> were thirty cors of the finest flour and sixty cors of meal,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>ten head of stall-fed cattle, twenty of pasture-fed cattle and a hundred sheep and goats, as well as deer, gazelles, roebucks and choice fowl.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8868AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8868AK\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>For he ruled over all the kingdoms west of the Euphrates River, from Tiphsah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8869AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8869AL\"></sup> to Gaza, and had peace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8869AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8869AM\"></sup> on all sides.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>During Solomon’s lifetime Judah and Israel, from Dan to Beersheba,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8870AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8870AN\"></sup> lived in safety,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8870AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8870AO\"></sup> everyone under their own vine and under their own fig tree.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8870AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8870AP\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Solomon had four thousand stalls for chariot horses,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8871AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8871AQ\"></sup> and twelve thousand horses.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The district governors,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8872AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8872AR\"></sup> each in his month, supplied provisions for King Solomon and all who came to the king’s table. They saw to it that nothing was lacking.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They also brought to the proper place their quotas of barley and straw for the chariot horses and the other horses.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>God gave Solomon wisdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8874AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8874AS\"></sup> and very great insight, and a breadth of understanding as measureless as the sand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8874AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8874AT\"></sup> on the seashore.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Solomon’s wisdom was greater than the wisdom of all the people of the East,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8875AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8875AU\"></sup> and greater than all the wisdom of Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8875AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8875AV\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>He was wiser<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8876AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8876AW\"></sup> than anyone else, including Ethan the Ezrahite—wiser than Heman, Kalkol and Darda, the sons of Mahol. And his fame spread to all the surrounding nations.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>He spoke three thousand proverbs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8877AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8877AX\"></sup> and his songs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8877AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8877AY\"></sup> numbered a thousand and five.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He spoke about plant life, from the cedar of Lebanon to the hyssop<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8878AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8878AZ\"></sup> that grows out of walls. He also spoke about animals and birds, reptiles and fish.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>From all nations people came to listen to Solomon’s wisdom, sent by all the kings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8879BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8879BA\"></sup> of the world, who had heard of his wisdom."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>When Hiram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8880B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8880B\"></sup> king of Tyre heard that Solomon had been anointed king to succeed his father David, he sent his envoys to Solomon, because he had always been on friendly terms with David.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Solomon sent back this message to Hiram:",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“You know that because of the wars<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8882C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8882C\"></sup> waged against my father David from all sides, he could not build<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8882D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8882D\"></sup> a temple for the Name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God until the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> put his enemies under his feet.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8882E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8882E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God has given me rest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8883F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8883F\"></sup> on every side, and there is no adversary<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8883G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8883G\"></sup> or disaster.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I intend, therefore, to build a temple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8884H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8884H\"></sup> for the Name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> told my father David, when he said, ‘Your son whom I will put on the throne in your place will build the temple for my Name.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8884I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8884I\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“So give orders that cedars<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8885J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8885J\"></sup> of Lebanon be cut for me. My men will work with yours, and I will pay you for your men whatever wages you set. You know that we have no one so skilled in felling timber as the Sidonians.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When Hiram heard Solomon’s message, he was greatly pleased and said, “Praise be to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8886K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8886K\"></sup> today, for he has given David a wise son to rule over this great nation.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Hiram sent word to Solomon:“I have received the message you sent me and will do all you want in providing the cedar and juniper logs.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>My men will haul them down from Lebanon to the Mediterranean Sea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8888L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8888L\"></sup>, and I will float them as rafts by sea to the place you specify. There I will separate them and you can take them away. And you are to grant my wish by providing food<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8888M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8888M\"></sup> for my royal household.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>In this way Hiram kept Solomon supplied with all the cedar and juniper logs he wanted,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and Solomon gave Hiram twenty thousand cors of wheat as food<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8890N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8890N\"></sup> for his household, in addition to twenty thousand baths of pressed olive oil. Solomon continued to do this for Hiram year after year.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave Solomon wisdom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8891O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8891O\"></sup> just as he had promised him. There were peaceful relations between Hiram and Solomon, and the two of them made a treaty.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8891P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8891P\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>King Solomon conscripted laborers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8892Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8892Q\"></sup> from all Israel—thirty thousand men.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He sent them off to Lebanon in shifts of ten thousand a month, so that they spent one month in Lebanon and two months at home. Adoniram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8893R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8893R\"></sup> was in charge of the forced labor.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Solomon had seventy thousand carriers and eighty thousand stonecutters in the hills,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>as well as thirty-three hundred foremen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8895S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8895S\"></sup> who supervised the project and directed the workers.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>At the king’s command they removed from the quarry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8896T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8896T\"></sup> large blocks of high-grade stone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8896U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8896U\"></sup> to provide a foundation of dressed stone for the temple.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The craftsmen of Solomon and Hiram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8897V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8897V\"></sup> and workers from Byblos<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8897W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8897W\"></sup> cut and prepared the timber and stone for the building of the temple."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>In the four hundred and eightieth year after the Israelites came out of Egypt, in the fourth year of Solomon’s reign over Israel, in the month of Ziv, the second month,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8898B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8898B\"></sup> he began to build the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8898C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8898C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The temple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8899D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8899D\"></sup> that King Solomon built for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was sixty cubits long, twenty wide and thirty high.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The portico<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8900E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8900E\"></sup> at the front of the main hall of the temple extended the width of the temple, that is twenty cubits, and projected ten cubits from the front of the temple.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He made narrow windows<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8901F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8901F\"></sup> high up in the temple walls.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Against the walls of the main hall and inner sanctuary he built a structure around the building, in which there were side rooms.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8902G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8902G\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The lowest floor was five cubits wide, the middle floor six cubits and the third floor seven. He made offset ledges around the outside of the temple so that nothing would be inserted into the temple walls.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>In building the temple, only blocks dressed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8904H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8904H\"></sup> at the quarry were used, and no hammer, chisel or any other iron tool<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8904I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8904I\"></sup> was heard at the temple site while it was being built.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The entrance to the lowest floor was on the south side of the temple; a stairway led up to the middle level and from there to the third.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So he built the temple and completed it, roofing it with beams and cedar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8906J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8906J\"></sup> planks.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And he built the side rooms all along the temple. The height of each was five cubits, and they were attached to the temple by beams of cedar.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8908K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8908K\"></sup> to Solomon:",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“As for this temple you are building, if you follow my decrees, observe my laws and keep all my commands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8909L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8909L\"></sup> and obey them, I will fulfill through you the promise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8909M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8909M\"></sup> I gave to David your father.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And I will live among the Israelites and will not abandon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8910N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8910N\"></sup> my people Israel.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So Solomon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8911O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8911O\"></sup> built the temple and completed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8911P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8911P\"></sup> it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He lined its interior walls with cedar boards, paneling them from the floor of the temple to the ceiling,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8912Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8912Q\"></sup> and covered the floor of the temple with planks of juniper.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8912R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8912R\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He partitioned off twenty cubits at the rear of the temple with cedar boards from floor to ceiling to form within the temple an inner sanctuary, the Most Holy Place.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8913S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8913S\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The main hall in front of this room was forty cubits long.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The inside of the temple was cedar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8915T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8915T\"></sup> carved with gourds and open flowers. Everything was cedar; no stone was to be seen.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He prepared the inner sanctuary<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8916U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8916U\"></sup> within the temple to set the ark of the covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8916V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8916V\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> there.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The inner sanctuary<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8917W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8917W\"></sup> was twenty cubits long, twenty wide and twenty high. He overlaid the inside with pure gold, and he also overlaid the altar of cedar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8917X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8917X\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Solomon covered the inside of the temple with pure gold, and he extended gold chains across the front of the inner sanctuary, which was overlaid with gold.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So he overlaid the whole interior with gold. He also overlaid with gold the altar that belonged to the inner sanctuary.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For the inner sanctuary he made a pair of cherubim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8920Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8920Y\"></sup> out of olive wood, each ten cubits high.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>One wing of the first cherub was five cubits long, and the other wing five cubits—ten cubits from wing tip to wing tip.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The second cherub also measured ten cubits, for the two cherubim were identical in size and shape.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The height of each cherub was ten cubits.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He placed the cherubim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8924Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8924Z\"></sup> inside the innermost room of the temple, with their wings spread out. The wing of one cherub touched one wall, while the wing of the other touched the other wall, and their wings touched each other in the middle of the room.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He overlaid the cherubim with gold.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>On the walls<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8926AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8926AA\"></sup> all around the temple, in both the inner and outer rooms, he carved cherubim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8926AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8926AB\"></sup> palm trees and open flowers.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>He also covered the floors of both the inner and outer rooms of the temple with gold.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For the entrance to the inner sanctuary he made doors out of olive wood that were one fifth of the width of the sanctuary.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And on the two olive-wood doors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8929AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8929AC\"></sup> he carved cherubim, palm trees and open flowers, and overlaid the cherubim and palm trees with hammered gold.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>In the same way, for the entrance to the main hall he made doorframes out of olive wood that were one fourth of the width of the hall.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>He also made two doors out of juniper wood, each having two leaves that turned in sockets.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>He carved cherubim, palm trees and open flowers on them and overlaid them with gold hammered evenly over the carvings.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And he built the inner courtyard<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8933AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8933AD\"></sup> of three courses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8933AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8933AE\"></sup> of dressed stone and one course of trimmed cedar beams.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>The foundation of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was laid in the fourth year, in the month of Ziv.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>In the eleventh year in the month of Bul, the eighth month, the temple was finished in all its details<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8935AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8935AF\"></sup> according to its specifications.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8935AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8935AG\"></sup> He had spent seven years building it."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>It took Solomon thirteen years, however, to complete the construction of his palace.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8936A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8936A\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He built the Palace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8937B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8937B\"></sup> of the Forest of Lebanon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8937C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8937C\"></sup> a hundred cubits long, fifty wide and thirty high, with four rows of cedar columns supporting trimmed cedar beams.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>It was roofed with cedar above the beams that rested on the columns—forty-five beams, fifteen to a row.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Its windows were placed high in sets of three, facing each other.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>All the doorways had rectangular frames; they were in the front part in sets of three, facing each other.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He made a colonnade fifty cubits long and thirty wide. In front of it was a portico, and in front of that were pillars and an overhanging roof.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He built the throne hall, the Hall of Justice, where he was to judge,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8942D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8942D\"></sup> and he covered it with cedar from floor to ceiling.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8942E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8942E\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the palace in which he was to live, set farther back, was similar in design. Solomon also made a palace like this hall for Pharaoh’s daughter, whom he had married.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8943F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8943F\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>All these structures, from the outside to the great courtyard and from foundation to eaves, were made of blocks of high-grade stone cut to size and smoothed on their inner and outer faces.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The foundations were laid with large stones of good quality, some measuring ten cubits and some eight.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Above were high-grade stones, cut to size, and cedar beams.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The great courtyard was surrounded by a wall of three courses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8947G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8947G\"></sup> of dressed stone and one course of trimmed cedar beams, as was the inner courtyard of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with its portico.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>King Solomon sent to Tyre and brought Huram,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8948J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8948J\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>whose mother was a widow from the tribe of Naphtali and whose father was from Tyre and a skilled craftsman in bronze. Huram was filled with wisdom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8949K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8949K\"></sup> with understanding and with knowledge to do all kinds of bronze work. He came to King Solomon and did all<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8949L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8949L\"></sup> the work assigned to him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He cast two bronze pillars,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8950M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8950M\"></sup> each eighteen cubits high and twelve cubits in circumference.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He also made two capitals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8951N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8951N\"></sup> of cast bronze to set on the tops of the pillars; each capital was five cubits high.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>A network of interwoven chains adorned the capitals on top of the pillars, seven for each capital.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He made pomegranates in two rows encircling each network to decorate the capitals on top of the pillars. He did the same for each capital.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The capitals on top of the pillars in the portico were in the shape of lilies, four cubits high.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>On the capitals of both pillars, above the bowl-shaped part next to the network, were the two hundred pomegranates<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8955O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8955O\"></sup> in rows all around.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He erected the pillars at the portico of the temple. The pillar to the south he named Jakin and the one to the north Boaz.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8956P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8956P\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The capitals on top were in the shape of lilies. And so the work on the pillars<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8957Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8957Q\"></sup> was completed.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He made the Sea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8958R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8958R\"></sup> of cast metal, circular in shape, measuring ten cubits from rim to rim and five cubits high. It took a line<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8958S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8958S\"></sup> of thirty cubits to measure around it.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Below the rim, gourds encircled it—ten to a cubit. The gourds were cast in two rows in one piece with the Sea.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The Sea stood on twelve bulls,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8960T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8960T\"></sup> three facing north, three facing west, three facing south and three facing east. The Sea rested on top of them, and their hindquarters were toward the center.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>It was a handbreadth in thickness, and its rim was like the rim of a cup, like a lily blossom. It held two thousand baths.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He also made ten movable stands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8962U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8962U\"></sup> of bronze; each was four cubits long, four wide and three high.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>This is how the stands were made: They had side panels attached to uprights.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>On the panels between the uprights were lions, bulls and cherubim—and on the uprights as well. Above and below the lions and bulls were wreaths of hammered work.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Each stand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8965V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8965V\"></sup> had four bronze wheels with bronze axles, and each had a basin resting on four supports, cast with wreaths on each side.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>On the inside of the stand there was an opening that had a circular frame one cubit deep. This opening was round, and with its basework it measured a cubit and a half. Around its opening there was engraving. The panels of the stands were square, not round.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The four wheels were under the panels, and the axles of the wheels were attached to the stand. The diameter of each wheel was a cubit and a half.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The wheels were made like chariot wheels; the axles, rims, spokes and hubs were all of cast metal.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Each stand had four handles, one on each corner, projecting from the stand.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>At the top of the stand there was a circular band half a cubit deep. The supports and panels were attached to the top of the stand.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>He engraved cherubim, lions and palm trees on the surfaces of the supports and on the panels, in every available space, with wreaths all around.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>This is the way he made the ten stands. They were all cast in the same molds and were identical in size and shape.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>He then made ten bronze basins,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8973W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8973W\"></sup> each holding forty baths and measuring four cubits across, one basin to go on each of the ten stands.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>He placed five of the stands on the south side of the temple and five on the north. He placed the Sea on the south side, at the southeast corner of the temple.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>He also made the pots and shovels and sprinkling bowls.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8975X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8975X\"></sup>So Huram finished all the work he had undertaken for King Solomon in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>:",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>the two pillars;the two bowl-shaped capitals on top of the pillars;the two sets of network decorating the two bowl-shaped capitals on top of the pillars;",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>the four hundred pomegranates for the two sets of network (two rows of pomegranates for each network decorating the bowl-shaped capitals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8977Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8977Y\"></sup> on top of the pillars);",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>the ten stands with their ten basins;",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>the Sea and the twelve bulls under it;",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>the pots, shovels and sprinkling bowls.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8980Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8980Z\"></sup>All these objects that Huram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8980AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8980AA\"></sup> made for King Solomon for the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> were of burnished bronze.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>The king had them cast in clay molds in the plain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8981AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8981AB\"></sup> of the Jordan between Sukkoth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8981AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8981AC\"></sup> and Zarethan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8981AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8981AD\"></sup>",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Solomon left all these things unweighed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8982AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8982AE\"></sup> because there were so many;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8982AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8982AF\"></sup> the weight of the bronze<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8982AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8982AG\"></sup> was not determined.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Solomon also made all<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8983AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8983AH\"></sup> the furnishings that were in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s temple:the golden altar;the golden table<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8983AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8983AI\"></sup> on which was the bread of the Presence;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8983AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8983AJ\"></sup>",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>the lampstands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8984AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8984AK\"></sup> of pure gold (five on the right and five on the left, in front of the inner sanctuary);the gold floral work and lamps and tongs;",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>the pure gold basins, wick trimmers, sprinkling bowls, dishes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8985AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8985AL\"></sup> and censers;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8985AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8985AM\"></sup>and the gold sockets for the doors of the innermost room, the Most Holy Place, and also for the doors of the main hall of the temple.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>When all the work King Solomon had done for the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was finished, he brought in the things his father David had dedicated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8986AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8986AN\"></sup>—the silver and gold and the furnishings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8986AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8986AO\"></sup>—and he placed them in the treasuries of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s temple."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>Then King Solomon summoned into his presence at Jerusalem the elders of Israel, all the heads of the tribes and the chiefs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8987B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8987B\"></sup> of the Israelite families, to bring up the ark<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8987C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8987C\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s covenant from Zion, the City of David.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8987D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8987D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>All the Israelites came together to King Solomon at the time of the festival<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8988E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8988E\"></sup> in the month of Ethanim, the seventh month.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8988F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8988F\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When all the elders of Israel had arrived, the priests<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8989G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8989G\"></sup> took up the ark,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and they brought up the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the tent of meeting<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8990H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8990H\"></sup> and all the sacred furnishings in it. The priests and Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8990I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8990I\"></sup> carried them up,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and King Solomon and the entire assembly of Israel that had gathered about him were before the ark, sacrificing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8991J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8991J\"></sup> so many sheep and cattle that they could not be recorded or counted.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The priests then brought the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8992K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8992K\"></sup> to its place in the inner sanctuary of the temple, the Most Holy Place,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8992L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8992L\"></sup> and put it beneath the wings of the cherubim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8992M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8992M\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The cherubim spread their wings over the place of the ark and overshadowed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8993N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8993N\"></sup> the ark and its carrying poles.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>These poles were so long that their ends could be seen from the Holy Place in front of the inner sanctuary, but not from outside the Holy Place; and they are still there today.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8994O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8994O\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>There was nothing in the ark except the two stone tablets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8995P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8995P\"></sup> that Moses had placed in it at Horeb, where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made a covenant with the Israelites after they came out of Egypt.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When the priests withdrew from the Holy Place, the cloud<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8996Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8996Q\"></sup> filled the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the priests could not perform their service<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8997R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8997R\"></sup> because of the cloud, for the glory<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8997S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8997S\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> filled his temple.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Solomon said, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has said that he would dwell in a dark cloud;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8998T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8998T\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I have indeed built a magnificent temple for you, a place for you to dwell<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8999U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8999U\"></sup> forever.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>While the whole assembly of Israel was standing there, the king turned around and blessed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9000V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9000V\"></sup> them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then he said:“Praise be to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9001W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9001W\"></sup> the God of Israel, who with his own hand has fulfilled what he promised with his own mouth to my father David. For he said,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>‘Since the day I brought my people Israel out of Egypt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9002X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9002X\"></sup> I have not chosen a city in any tribe of Israel to have a temple built so that my Name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9002Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9002Y\"></sup> might be there, but I have chosen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9002Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9002Z\"></sup> David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9002AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9002AA\"></sup> to rule my people Israel.’",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“My father David had it in his heart<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9003AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9003AB\"></sup> to build a temple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9003AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9003AC\"></sup> for the Name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to my father David, ‘You did well to have it in your heart to build a temple for my Name.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Nevertheless, you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9005AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9005AD\"></sup> are not the one to build the temple, but your son, your own flesh and blood—he is the one who will build the temple for my Name.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9005AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9005AE\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has kept the promise he made: I have succeeded<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9006AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9006AF\"></sup> David my father and now I sit on the throne of Israel, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> promised, and I have built<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9006AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9006AG\"></sup> the temple for the Name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>I have provided a place there for the ark, in which is the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that he made with our ancestors when he brought them out of Egypt.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Solomon stood before the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in front of the whole assembly of Israel, spread out his hands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9008AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9008AI\"></sup> toward heaven",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and said:“<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, there is no God like<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9009AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9009AJ\"></sup> you in heaven above or on earth below—you who keep your covenant of love<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9009AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9009AK\"></sup> with your servants who continue wholeheartedly in your way.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>You have kept your promise to your servant David my father; with your mouth you have promised and with your hand you have fulfilled it—as it is today.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“Now <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, keep for your servant David my father the promises<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9011AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9011AL\"></sup> you made to him when you said, ‘You shall never fail to have a successor to sit before me on the throne of Israel, if only your descendants are careful in all they do to walk before me faithfully as you have done.’",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And now, God of Israel, let your word that you promised<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9012AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9012AM\"></sup> your servant David my father come true.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“But will God really dwell<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9013AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9013AN\"></sup> on earth? The heavens, even the highest heaven,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9013AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9013AO\"></sup> cannot contain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9013AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9013AP\"></sup> you. How much less this temple I have built!",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Yet give attention to your servant’s prayer and his plea for mercy, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God. Hear the cry and the prayer that your servant is praying in your presence this day.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>May your eyes be open<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9015AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9015AQ\"></sup> toward<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9015AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9015AR\"></sup> this temple night and day, this place of which you said, ‘My Name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9015AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9015AS\"></sup> shall be there,’ so that you will hear the prayer your servant prays toward this place.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Hear the supplication of your servant and of your people Israel when they pray<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9016AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9016AT\"></sup> toward this place. Hear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9016AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9016AU\"></sup> from heaven, your dwelling place, and when you hear, forgive.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9016AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9016AV\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“When anyone wrongs their neighbor and is required to take an oath and they come and swear the oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9017AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9017AW\"></sup> before your altar in this temple,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>then hear from heaven and act. Judge between your servants, condemning the guilty by bringing down on their heads what they have done, and vindicating the innocent by treating them in accordance with their innocence.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9018AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9018AX\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“When your people Israel have been defeated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9019AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9019AY\"></sup> by an enemy because they have sinned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9019AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9019AZ\"></sup> against you, and when they turn back to you and give praise to your name, praying and making supplication to you in this temple,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9019BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9019BA\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>then hear from heaven and forgive the sin of your people Israel and bring them back to the land you gave to their ancestors.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>“When the heavens are shut up and there is no rain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9021BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9021BB\"></sup> because your people have sinned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9021BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9021BC\"></sup> against you, and when they pray toward this place and give praise to your name and turn from their sin because you have afflicted them,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>then hear from heaven and forgive the sin of your servants, your people Israel. Teach<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9022BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9022BD\"></sup> them the right way<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9022BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9022BE\"></sup> to live, and send rain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9022BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9022BF\"></sup> on the land you gave your people for an inheritance.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>“When famine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9023BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9023BG\"></sup> or plague<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9023BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9023BH\"></sup> comes to the land, or blight<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9023BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9023BI\"></sup> or mildew, locusts or grasshoppers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9023BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9023BJ\"></sup> or when an enemy besieges them in any of their cities, whatever disaster or disease may come,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>and when a prayer or plea is made by anyone among your people Israel—being aware of the afflictions of their own hearts, and spreading out their hands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9024BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9024BK\"></sup> toward this temple—",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>then hear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9025BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9025BL\"></sup> from heaven, your dwelling place. Forgive<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9025BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9025BM\"></sup> and act; deal with everyone according to all they do, since you know<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9025BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9025BN\"></sup> their hearts (for you alone know every human heart),",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>so that they will fear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9026BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9026BO\"></sup> you all the time they live in the land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9026BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9026BP\"></sup> you gave our ancestors.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>“As for the foreigner<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9027BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9027BQ\"></sup> who does not belong to your people Israel but has come from a distant land because of your name—",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>for they will hear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9028BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9028BR\"></sup> of your great name and your mighty hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9028BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9028BS\"></sup> and your outstretched arm—when they come and pray toward this temple,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>then hear from heaven, your dwelling place. Do whatever the foreigner asks of you, so that all the peoples of the earth may know<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9029BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9029BT\"></sup> your name and fear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9029BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9029BU\"></sup> you, as do your own people Israel, and may know that this house I have built bears your Name.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9029BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9029BV\"></sup>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>“When your people go to war against their enemies, wherever you send them, and when they pray<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9030BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9030BW\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> toward the city you have chosen and the temple I have built for your Name,",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>then hear from heaven their prayer and their plea, and uphold their cause.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9031BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9031BX\"></sup>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>“When they sin against you—for there is no one who does not sin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9032BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9032BY\"></sup>—and you become angry with them and give them over to their enemies, who take them captive<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9032BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9032BZ\"></sup> to their own lands, far away or near;",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>and if they have a change of heart in the land where they are held captive, and repent and plead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9033CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9033CA\"></sup> with you in the land of their captors and say, ‘We have sinned, we have done wrong, we have acted wickedly’;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9033CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9033CB\"></sup>",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>and if they turn back<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9034CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9034CC\"></sup> to you with all their heart<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9034CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9034CD\"></sup> and soul in the land of their enemies who took them captive, and pray<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9034CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9034CE\"></sup> to you toward the land you gave their ancestors, toward the city you have chosen and the temple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9034CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9034CF\"></sup> I have built for your Name;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9034CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9034CG\"></sup>",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>then from heaven, your dwelling place, hear their prayer and their plea, and uphold their cause.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>And forgive your people, who have sinned against you; forgive all the offenses they have committed against you, and cause their captors to show them mercy;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9036CH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CH&quot;&gt;CH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9036CH\"></sup>",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>for they are your people and your inheritance,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9037CI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CI&quot;&gt;CI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9037CI\"></sup> whom you brought out of Egypt, out of that iron-smelting furnace.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9037CJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CJ&quot;&gt;CJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9037CJ\"></sup>",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>“May your eyes be open<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9038CK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CK&quot;&gt;CK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9038CK\"></sup> to your servant’s plea and to the plea of your people Israel, and may you listen to them whenever they cry out to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9038CL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CL&quot;&gt;CL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9038CL\"></sup>",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>For you singled them out from all the nations of the world to be your own inheritance,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9039CM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CM&quot;&gt;CM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9039CM\"></sup> just as you declared through your servant Moses when you, Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, brought our ancestors out of Egypt.”",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>When Solomon had finished all these prayers and supplications to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he rose from before the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, where he had been kneeling with his hands spread out toward heaven.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>He stood and blessed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9041CN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CN&quot;&gt;CN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9041CN\"></sup> the whole assembly of Israel in a loud voice, saying:",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>“Praise be to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who has given rest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9042CO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CO&quot;&gt;CO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9042CO\"></sup> to his people Israel just as he promised. Not one word has failed of all the good promises<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9042CP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CP&quot;&gt;CP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9042CP\"></sup> he gave through his servant Moses.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God be with us as he was with our ancestors; may he never leave us nor forsake<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9043CQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CQ&quot;&gt;CQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9043CQ\"></sup> us.",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>May he turn our hearts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9044CR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CR&quot;&gt;CR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9044CR\"></sup> to him, to walk in obedience to him and keep the commands, decrees and laws he gave our ancestors.",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>And may these words of mine, which I have prayed before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, be near to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God day and night, that he may uphold the cause of his servant and the cause of his people Israel according to each day’s need,",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>so that all the peoples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9046CS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CS&quot;&gt;CS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9046CS\"></sup> of the earth may know that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is God and that there is no other.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9046CT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CT&quot;&gt;CT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9046CT\"></sup>",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>And may your hearts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9047CU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CU&quot;&gt;CU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9047CU\"></sup> be fully committed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9047CV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CV&quot;&gt;CV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9047CV\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, to live by his decrees and obey his commands, as at this time.”",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>Then the king and all Israel with him offered sacrifices<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9048CX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CX&quot;&gt;CX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9048CX\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>Solomon offered a sacrifice of fellowship offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: twenty-two thousand cattle and a hundred and twenty thousand sheep and goats. So the king and all the Israelites dedicated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9049CY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CY&quot;&gt;CY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9049CY\"></sup> the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>On that same day the king consecrated the middle part of the courtyard in front of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and there he offered burnt offerings, grain offerings and the fat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9050CZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CZ&quot;&gt;CZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9050CZ\"></sup> of the fellowship offerings, because the bronze altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9050DA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DA&quot;&gt;DA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9050DA\"></sup> that stood before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was too small to hold the burnt offerings, the grain offerings and the fat of the fellowship offerings.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9050DB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DB&quot;&gt;DB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9050DB\"></sup>",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>So Solomon observed the festival<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9051DC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DC&quot;&gt;DC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9051DC\"></sup> at that time, and all Israel with him—a vast assembly, people from Lebo Hamath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9051DD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DD&quot;&gt;DD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9051DD\"></sup> to the Wadi of Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9051DE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DE&quot;&gt;DE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9051DE\"></sup> They celebrated it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God for seven days and seven days more, fourteen days in all.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>On the following day he sent the people away. They blessed the king and then went home, joyful and glad in heart for all the good<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9052DF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DF&quot;&gt;DF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9052DF\"></sup> things the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had done for his servant David and his people Israel."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>When Solomon had finished<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9053B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9053B\"></sup> building the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the royal palace, and had achieved all he had desired to do,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9054C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9054C\"></sup> to him a second time, as he had appeared to him at Gibeon.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him:“I have heard<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9055D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9055D\"></sup> the prayer and plea you have made before me; I have consecrated this temple, which you have built, by putting my Name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9055E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9055E\"></sup> there forever. My eyes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9055F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9055F\"></sup> and my heart will always be there.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“As for you, if you walk before me faithfully with integrity of heart<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9056G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9056G\"></sup> and uprightness, as David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9056H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9056H\"></sup> your father did, and do all I command and observe my decrees and laws,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9056I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9056I\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I will establish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9057J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9057J\"></sup> your royal throne over Israel forever, as I promised David your father when I said, ‘You shall never fail<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9057K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9057K\"></sup> to have a successor on the throne of Israel.’",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“But if you or your descendants turn away<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9058L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9058L\"></sup> from me and do not observe the commands and decrees I have given you and go off to serve other gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9058M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9058M\"></sup> and worship them,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>then I will cut off Israel from the land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9059N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9059N\"></sup> I have given them and will reject this temple I have consecrated for my Name.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9059O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9059O\"></sup> Israel will then become a byword<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9059P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9059P\"></sup> and an object of ridicule<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9059Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9059Q\"></sup> among all peoples.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>This temple will become a heap of rubble. All who pass by will be appalled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9060R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9060R\"></sup> and will scoff and say, ‘Why has the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> done such a thing to this land and to this temple?’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9060S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9060S\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>People will answer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9061T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9061T\"></sup> ‘Because they have forsaken<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9061U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9061U\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God, who brought their ancestors out of Egypt, and have embraced other gods, worshiping and serving them—that is why the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought all this disaster<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9061V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9061V\"></sup> on them.’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>At the end of twenty years, during which Solomon built these two buildings—the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the royal palace—",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>King Solomon gave twenty towns in Galilee to Hiram king of Tyre, because Hiram had supplied him with all the cedar and juniper and gold<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9063X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9063X\"></sup> he wanted.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But when Hiram went from Tyre to see the towns that Solomon had given him, he was not pleased with them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“What kind of towns are these you have given me, my brother?” he asked. And he called them the Land of Kabul,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9065Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9065Y\"></sup> a name they have to this day.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now Hiram had sent to the king 120 talents of gold.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9066Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9066Z\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Here is the account of the forced labor King Solomon conscripted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9067AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9067AA\"></sup> to build the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s temple, his own palace, the terraces,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9067AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9067AB\"></sup> the wall of Jerusalem, and Hazor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9067AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9067AC\"></sup> Megiddo and Gezer.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9067AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9067AD\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>(Pharaoh king of Egypt had attacked and captured Gezer. He had set it on fire. He killed its Canaanite inhabitants and then gave it as a wedding gift to his daughter,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9068AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9068AE\"></sup> Solomon’s wife.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And Solomon rebuilt Gezer.) He built up Lower Beth Horon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9069AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9069AF\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Baalath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9070AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9070AG\"></sup> and Tadmor in the desert, within his land,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>as well as all his store cities<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9071AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9071AH\"></sup> and the towns for his chariots<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9071AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9071AI\"></sup> and for his horses—whatever he desired to build in Jerusalem, in Lebanon and throughout all the territory he ruled.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>There were still people left from the Amorites, Hittites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9072AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9072AJ\"></sup> Perizzites, Hivites and Jebusites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9072AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9072AK\"></sup> (these peoples were not Israelites).",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Solomon conscripted the descendants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9073AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9073AL\"></sup> of all these peoples remaining in the land—whom the Israelites could not exterminate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9073AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9073AM\"></sup>—to serve as slave labor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9073AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9073AN\"></sup> as it is to this day.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But Solomon did not make slaves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9074AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9074AO\"></sup> of any of the Israelites; they were his fighting men, his government officials, his officers, his captains, and the commanders of his chariots and charioteers.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>They were also the chief officials<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9075AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9075AP\"></sup> in charge of Solomon’s projects—550 officials supervising those who did the work.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>After Pharaoh’s daughter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9076AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9076AQ\"></sup> had come up from the City of David to the palace Solomon had built for her, he constructed the terraces.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9076AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9076AR\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Three<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9077AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9077AS\"></sup> times a year Solomon sacrificed burnt offerings and fellowship offerings on the altar he had built for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, burning incense before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> along with them, and so fulfilled the temple obligations.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>King Solomon also built ships<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9078AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9078AT\"></sup> at Ezion Geber,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9078AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9078AU\"></sup> which is near Elath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9078AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9078AV\"></sup> in Edom, on the shore of the Red Sea.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And Hiram sent his men—sailors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9079AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9079AW\"></sup> who knew the sea—to serve in the fleet with Solomon’s men.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They sailed to Ophir<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9080AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9080AX\"></sup> and brought back 420 talents of gold,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9080AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9080AY\"></sup> which they delivered to King Solomon."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>When the queen of Sheba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9081B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9081B\"></sup> heard about the fame<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9081C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9081C\"></sup> of Solomon and his relationship to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, she came to test Solomon with hard questions.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9081D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9081D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Arriving at Jerusalem with a very great caravan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9082E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9082E\"></sup>—with camels carrying spices, large quantities of gold, and precious stones—she came to Solomon and talked with him about all that she had on her mind.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Solomon answered all her questions; nothing was too hard for the king to explain to her.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When the queen of Sheba saw all the wisdom of Solomon and the palace he had built,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>the food on his table,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9085F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9085F\"></sup> the seating of his officials, the attending servants in their robes, his cupbearers, and the burnt offerings he made at the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, she was overwhelmed.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>She said to the king, “The report I heard in my own country about your achievements and your wisdom is true.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But I did not believe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9087G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9087G\"></sup> these things until I came and saw with my own eyes. Indeed, not even half was told me; in wisdom and wealth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9087H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9087H\"></sup> you have far exceeded the report I heard.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>How happy your people must be! How happy your officials, who continually stand before you and hear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9088I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9088I\"></sup> your wisdom!",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Praise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9089J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9089J\"></sup> be to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who has delighted in you and placed you on the throne of Israel. Because of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s eternal love<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9089K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9089K\"></sup> for Israel, he has made you king to maintain justice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9089L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9089L\"></sup> and righteousness.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And she gave the king 120 talents of gold,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9090M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9090M\"></sup> large quantities of spices, and precious stones. Never again were so many spices brought in as those the queen of Sheba gave to King Solomon.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>(Hiram’s ships brought gold from Ophir;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9091N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9091N\"></sup> and from there they brought great cargoes of almugwood and precious stones.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The king used the almugwood to make supports for the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and for the royal palace, and to make harps and lyres for the musicians. So much almugwood has never been imported or seen since that day.)",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>King Solomon gave the queen of Sheba all she desired and asked for, besides what he had given her out of his royal bounty. Then she left and returned with her retinue to her own country.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The weight of the gold<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9094P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9094P\"></sup> that Solomon received yearly was 666 talents,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>not including the revenues from merchants and traders and from all the Arabian kings and the governors of the territories.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>King Solomon made two hundred large shields<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9096Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9096Q\"></sup> of hammered gold; six hundred shekels of gold went into each shield.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He also made three hundred small shields of hammered gold, with three minas of gold in each shield. The king put them in the Palace of the Forest of Lebanon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9097R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9097R\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then the king made a great throne covered with ivory and overlaid with fine gold.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The throne had six steps, and its back had a rounded top. On both sides of the seat were armrests, with a lion standing beside each of them.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Twelve lions stood on the six steps, one at either end of each step. Nothing like it had ever been made for any other kingdom.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>All King Solomon’s goblets were gold, and all the household articles in the Palace of the Forest of Lebanon were pure gold.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9101S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9101S\"></sup> Nothing was made of silver, because silver was considered of little value in Solomon’s days.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The king had a fleet of trading ships<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9102T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9102T\"></sup> at sea along with the ships<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9102U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9102U\"></sup> of Hiram. Once every three years it returned, carrying gold, silver and ivory, and apes and baboons.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>King Solomon was greater in riches<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9103V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9103V\"></sup> and wisdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9103W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9103W\"></sup> than all the other kings of the earth.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The whole world sought audience with Solomon to hear the wisdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9104X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9104X\"></sup> God had put in his heart.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Year after year, everyone who came brought a gift<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9105Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9105Y\"></sup>—articles of silver and gold, robes, weapons and spices, and horses and mules.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Solomon accumulated chariots and horses;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9106Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9106Z\"></sup> he had fourteen hundred chariots and twelve thousand horses, which he kept in the chariot cities and also with him in Jerusalem.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The king made silver as common<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9107AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9107AA\"></sup> in Jerusalem as stones,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9107AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9107AB\"></sup> and cedar as plentiful as sycamore-fig<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9107AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9107AC\"></sup> trees in the foothills.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Solomon’s horses were imported from Egypt and from Kue—the royal merchants purchased them from Kue at the current price.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>They imported a chariot from Egypt for six hundred shekels of silver, and a horse for a hundred and fifty. They also exported them to all the kings of the Hittites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9109AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9109AD\"></sup> and of the Arameans."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>King Solomon, however, loved many foreign women<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9110A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9110A\"></sup> besides Pharaoh’s daughter—Moabites, Ammonites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9110B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9110B\"></sup> Edomites, Sidonians and Hittites.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>They were from nations about which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had told the Israelites, “You must not intermarry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9111C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9111C\"></sup> with them, because they will surely turn your hearts after their gods.” Nevertheless, Solomon held fast to them in love.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He had seven hundred wives of royal birth and three hundred concubines,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9112D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9112D\"></sup> and his wives led him astray.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9112E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9112E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>As Solomon grew old, his wives turned his heart after other gods,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9113F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9113F\"></sup> and his heart was not fully devoted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9113G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9113G\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God, as the heart of David his father had been.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He followed Ashtoreth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9114H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9114H\"></sup> the goddess of the Sidonians, and Molek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9114I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9114I\"></sup> the detestable god of the Ammonites.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Solomon did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9115J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9115J\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; he did not follow the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> completely, as David his father had done.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>On a hill east<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9116K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9116K\"></sup> of Jerusalem, Solomon built a high place for Chemosh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9116L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9116L\"></sup> the detestable god of Moab, and for Molek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9116M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9116M\"></sup> the detestable god of the Ammonites.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He did the same for all his foreign wives, who burned incense and offered sacrifices to their gods.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> became angry with Solomon because his heart had turned away from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, who had appeared<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9118N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9118N\"></sup> to him twice.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Although he had forbidden Solomon to follow other gods,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9119O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9119O\"></sup> Solomon did not keep the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s command.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9119P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9119P\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Solomon, “Since this is your attitude and you have not kept my covenant and my decrees,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9120Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9120Q\"></sup> which I commanded you, I will most certainly tear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9120R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9120R\"></sup> the kingdom away from you and give it to one of your subordinates.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Nevertheless, for the sake of David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9121S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9121S\"></sup> your father, I will not do it during your lifetime. I will tear it out of the hand of your son.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Yet I will not tear the whole kingdom from him, but will give him one tribe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9122T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9122T\"></sup> for the sake<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9122U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9122U\"></sup> of David my servant and for the sake of Jerusalem, which I have chosen.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9122V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9122V\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> raised up against Solomon an adversary,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9123W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9123W\"></sup> Hadad the Edomite, from the royal line of Edom.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Earlier when David was fighting with Edom, Joab the commander of the army, who had gone up to bury the dead, had struck down all the men in Edom.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9124X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9124X\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Joab and all the Israelites stayed there for six months, until they had destroyed all the men in Edom.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But Hadad, still only a boy, fled to Egypt with some Edomite officials who had served his father.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They set out from Midian and went to Paran.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9127Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9127Y\"></sup> Then taking people from Paran with them, they went to Egypt, to Pharaoh king of Egypt, who gave Hadad a house and land and provided him with food.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Pharaoh was so pleased with Hadad that he gave him a sister of his own wife, Queen Tahpenes, in marriage.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The sister of Tahpenes bore him a son named Genubath, whom Tahpenes brought up in the royal palace. There Genubath lived with Pharaoh’s own children.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>While he was in Egypt, Hadad heard that David rested with his ancestors and that Joab the commander of the army was also dead. Then Hadad said to Pharaoh, “Let me go, that I may return to my own country.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“What have you lacked here that you want to go back to your own country?” Pharaoh asked.“Nothing,” Hadad replied, “but do let me go!”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And God raised up against Solomon another adversary,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9132Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9132Z\"></sup> Rezon son of Eliada, who had fled from his master, Hadadezer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9132AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9132AA\"></sup> king of Zobah.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When David destroyed Zobah’s army, Rezon gathered a band of men around him and became their leader; they went to Damascus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9133AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9133AB\"></sup> where they settled and took control.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Rezon was Israel’s adversary as long as Solomon lived, adding to the trouble caused by Hadad. So Rezon ruled in Aram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9134AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9134AC\"></sup> and was hostile toward Israel.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Also, Jeroboam son of Nebat rebelled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9135AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9135AD\"></sup> against the king. He was one of Solomon’s officials, an Ephraimite from Zeredah, and his mother was a widow named Zeruah.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Here is the account of how he rebelled against the king: Solomon had built the terraces<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9136AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9136AE\"></sup> and had filled in the gap in the wall of the city of David his father.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now Jeroboam was a man of standing,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9137AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9137AF\"></sup> and when Solomon saw how well<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9137AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9137AG\"></sup> the young man did his work, he put him in charge of the whole labor force of the tribes of Joseph.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>About that time Jeroboam was going out of Jerusalem, and Ahijah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9138AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9138AH\"></sup> the prophet of Shiloh met him on the way, wearing a new cloak. The two of them were alone out in the country,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>and Ahijah took hold of the new cloak he was wearing and tore<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9139AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9139AI\"></sup> it into twelve pieces.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then he said to Jeroboam, “Take ten pieces for yourself, for this is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, says: ‘See, I am going to tear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9140AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9140AJ\"></sup> the kingdom out of Solomon’s hand and give you ten tribes.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But for the sake<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9141AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9141AK\"></sup> of my servant David and the city of Jerusalem, which I have chosen out of all the tribes of Israel, he will have one tribe.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>I will do this because they have forsaken me and worshiped<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9142AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9142AL\"></sup> Ashtoreth the goddess of the Sidonians, Chemosh the god of the Moabites, and Molek the god of the Ammonites, and have not walked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9142AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9142AM\"></sup> in obedience to me, nor done what is right in my eyes, nor kept my decrees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9142AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9142AN\"></sup> and laws as David, Solomon’s father, did.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“‘But I will not take the whole kingdom out of Solomon’s hand; I have made him ruler all the days of his life for the sake of David my servant, whom I chose and who obeyed my commands and decrees.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>I will take the kingdom from his son’s hands and give you ten tribes.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>I will give one tribe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9145AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9145AO\"></sup> to his son so that David my servant may always have a lamp<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9145AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9145AP\"></sup> before me in Jerusalem, the city where I chose to put my Name.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>However, as for you, I will take you, and you will rule<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9146AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9146AQ\"></sup> over all that your heart desires;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9146AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9146AR\"></sup> you will be king over Israel.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>If you do whatever I command you and walk in obedience to me and do what is right<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9147AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9147AS\"></sup> in my eyes by obeying my decrees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9147AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9147AT\"></sup> and commands, as David my servant did, I will be with you. I will build you a dynasty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9147AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9147AU\"></sup> as enduring as the one I built for David and will give Israel to you.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>I will humble David’s descendants because of this, but not forever.’”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Solomon tried to kill Jeroboam, but Jeroboam fled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9149AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9149AV\"></sup> to Egypt, to Shishak<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9149AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9149AW\"></sup> the king, and stayed there until Solomon’s death.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>As for the other events of Solomon’s reign—all he did and the wisdom he displayed—are they not written in the book of the annals of Solomon?",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Solomon reigned in Jerusalem over all Israel forty years.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Then he rested with his ancestors and was buried in the city of David his father. And Rehoboam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9152AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9152AY\"></sup> his son succeeded him as king."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>Rehoboam went to Shechem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9153B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9153B\"></sup> for all Israel had gone there to make him king.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When Jeroboam son of Nebat heard this (he was still in Egypt, where he had fled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9154C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9154C\"></sup> from King Solomon), he returned from Egypt.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So they sent for Jeroboam, and he and the whole assembly of Israel went to Rehoboam and said to him:",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Your father put a heavy yoke<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9156D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9156D\"></sup> on us, but now lighten the harsh labor and the heavy yoke he put on us, and we will serve you.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Rehoboam answered, “Go away for three days and then come back to me.” So the people went away.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then King Rehoboam consulted the elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9158E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9158E\"></sup> who had served his father Solomon during his lifetime. “How would you advise me to answer these people?” he asked.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They replied, “If today you will be a servant to these people and serve them and give them a favorable answer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9159F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9159F\"></sup> they will always be your servants.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But Rehoboam rejected<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9160G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9160G\"></sup> the advice the elders gave him and consulted the young men who had grown up with him and were serving him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He asked them, “What is your advice? How should we answer these people who say to me, ‘Lighten the yoke your father put on us’?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The young men who had grown up with him replied, “These people have said to you, ‘Your father put a heavy yoke on us, but make our yoke lighter.’ Now tell them, ‘My little finger is thicker than my father’s waist.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>My father laid on you a heavy yoke; I will make it even heavier. My father scourged you with whips; I will scourge you with scorpions.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Three days later Jeroboam and all the people returned to Rehoboam, as the king had said, “Come back to me in three days.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The king answered the people harshly. Rejecting the advice given him by the elders,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>he followed the advice of the young men and said, “My father made your yoke heavy; I will make it even heavier. My father scourged<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9166H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9166H\"></sup> you with whips; I will scourge you with scorpions.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So the king did not listen to the people, for this turn of events was from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9167I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9167I\"></sup> to fulfill the word the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had spoken to Jeroboam son of Nebat through Ahijah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9167J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9167J\"></sup> the Shilonite.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When all Israel saw that the king refused to listen to them, they answered the king:“What share<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9168K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9168K\"></sup> do we have in David,what part in Jesse’s son?To your tents, Israel!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9168L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9168L\"></sup>Look after your own house, David!”So the Israelites went home.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9168M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9168M\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But as for the Israelites who were living in the towns of Judah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9169N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9169N\"></sup> Rehoboam still ruled over them.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>King Rehoboam sent out Adoniram,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9170O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9170O\"></sup> who was in charge of forced labor, but all Israel stoned him to death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9170P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9170P\"></sup> King Rehoboam, however, managed to get into his chariot and escape to Jerusalem.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So Israel has been in rebellion against the house of David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9171Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9171Q\"></sup> to this day.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When all the Israelites heard that Jeroboam had returned, they sent and called him to the assembly and made him king over all Israel. Only the tribe of Judah remained loyal to the house of David.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9172R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9172R\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When Rehoboam arrived in Jerusalem, he mustered all Judah and the tribe of Benjamin—a hundred and eighty thousand able young men—to go to war<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9173S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9173S\"></sup> against Israel and to regain the kingdom for Rehoboam son of Solomon.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But this word of God came to Shemaiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9174T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9174T\"></sup> the man of God:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9174U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9174U\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Say to Rehoboam son of Solomon king of Judah, to all Judah and Benjamin, and to the rest of the people,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: Do not go up to fight against your brothers, the Israelites. Go home, every one of you, for this is my doing.’” So they obeyed the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and went home again, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had ordered.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Jeroboam fortified Shechem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9177V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9177V\"></sup> in the hill country of Ephraim and lived there. From there he went out and built up Peniel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9177W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9177W\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Jeroboam thought to himself, “The kingdom will now likely revert to the house of David.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>If these people go up to offer sacrifices at the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9179X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9179X\"></sup> they will again give their allegiance to their lord, Rehoboam king of Judah. They will kill me and return to King Rehoboam.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>After seeking advice, the king made two golden calves.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9180Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9180Y\"></sup> He said to the people, “It is too much for you to go up to Jerusalem. Here are your gods, Israel, who brought you up out of Egypt.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9180Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9180Z\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>One he set up in Bethel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9181AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9181AA\"></sup> and the other in Dan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9181AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9181AB\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And this thing became a sin;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9182AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9182AC\"></sup> the people came to worship the one at Bethel and went as far as Dan to worship the other.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Jeroboam built shrines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9183AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9183AD\"></sup> on high places and appointed priests<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9183AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9183AE\"></sup> from all sorts of people, even though they were not Levites.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>He instituted a festival on the fifteenth day of the eighth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9184AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9184AF\"></sup> month, like the festival held in Judah, and offered sacrifices on the altar. This he did in Bethel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9184AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9184AG\"></sup> sacrificing to the calves he had made. And at Bethel he also installed priests at the high places he had made.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>On the fifteenth day of the eighth month, a month of his own choosing, he offered sacrifices on the altar he had built at Bethel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9185AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9185AH\"></sup> So he instituted the festival for the Israelites and went up to the altar to make offerings."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>By the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> a man of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9186A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9186A\"></sup> came from Judah to Bethel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9186B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9186B\"></sup> as Jeroboam was standing by the altar to make an offering.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>By the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> he cried out against the altar: “Altar, altar! This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: ‘A son named Josiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9187C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9187C\"></sup> will be born to the house of David. On you he will sacrifice the priests of the high places<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9187D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9187D\"></sup> who make offerings here, and human bones will be burned on you.’”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>That same day the man of God gave a sign:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9188E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9188E\"></sup> “This is the sign the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has declared: The altar will be split apart and the ashes on it will be poured out.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When King Jeroboam heard what the man of God cried out against the altar at Bethel, he stretched out his hand from the altar and said, “Seize him!” But the hand he stretched out toward the man shriveled up, so that he could not pull it back.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Also, the altar was split apart and its ashes poured out according to the sign given by the man of God by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the king said to the man of God, “Intercede<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9191F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9191F\"></sup> with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and pray for me that my hand may be restored.” So the man of God interceded with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the king’s hand was restored and became as it was before.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The king said to the man of God, “Come home with me for a meal, and I will give you a gift.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9192G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9192G\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But the man of God answered the king, “Even if you were to give me half your possessions,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9193H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9193H\"></sup> I would not go with you, nor would I eat bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9193I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9193I\"></sup> or drink water here.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For I was commanded by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: ‘You must not eat bread or drink water or return by the way you came.’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So he took another road and did not return by the way he had come to Bethel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now there was a certain old prophet living in Bethel, whose sons came and told him all that the man of God had done there that day. They also told their father what he had said to the king.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Their father asked them, “Which way did he go?” And his sons showed him which road the man of God from Judah had taken.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So he said to his sons, “Saddle the donkey for me.” And when they had saddled the donkey for him, he mounted it",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and rode after the man of God. He found him sitting under an oak tree and asked, “Are you the man of God who came from Judah?”“I am,” he replied.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So the prophet said to him, “Come home with me and eat.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The man of God said, “I cannot turn back and go with you, nor can I eat bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9201J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9201J\"></sup> or drink water with you in this place.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I have been told by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: ‘You must not eat bread or drink water there or return by the way you came.’”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The old prophet answered, “I too am a prophet, as you are. And an angel said to me by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9203K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9203K\"></sup> ‘Bring him back with you to your house so that he may eat bread and drink water.’” (But he was lying<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9203L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9203L\"></sup> to him.)",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So the man of God returned with him and ate and drank in his house.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>While they were sitting at the table, the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to the old prophet who had brought him back.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He cried out to the man of God who had come from Judah, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: ‘You have defied<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9206M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9206M\"></sup> the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and have not kept the command the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gave you.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>You came back and ate bread and drank water in the place where he told you not to eat or drink. Therefore your body will not be buried in the tomb of your ancestors.’”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>When the man of God had finished eating and drinking, the prophet who had brought him back saddled his donkey for him.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>As he went on his way, a lion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9209N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9209N\"></sup> met him on the road and killed him, and his body was left lying on the road, with both the donkey and the lion standing beside it.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Some people who passed by saw the body lying there, with the lion standing beside the body, and they went and reported it in the city where the old prophet lived.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When the prophet who had brought him back from his journey heard of it, he said, “It is the man of God who defied<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9211O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9211O\"></sup> the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given him over to the lion, which has mauled him and killed him, as the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had warned him.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The prophet said to his sons, “Saddle the donkey for me,” and they did so.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then he went out and found the body lying on the road, with the donkey and the lion standing beside it. The lion had neither eaten the body nor mauled the donkey.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So the prophet picked up the body of the man of God, laid it on the donkey, and brought it back to his own city to mourn for him and bury him.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then he laid the body in his own tomb,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9215P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9215P\"></sup> and they mourned over him and said, “Alas, my brother!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9215Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9215Q\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>After burying him, he said to his sons, “When I die, bury me in the grave where the man of God is buried; lay my bones<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9216R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9216R\"></sup> beside his bones.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>For the message he declared by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> against the altar in Bethel and against all the shrines on the high places<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9217S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9217S\"></sup> in the towns of Samaria<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9217T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9217T\"></sup> will certainly come true.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9217U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9217U\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Even after this, Jeroboam did not change his evil ways,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9218V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9218V\"></sup> but once more appointed priests for the high places from all sorts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9218W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9218W\"></sup> of people. Anyone who wanted to become a priest he consecrated for the high places.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>This was the sin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9219X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9219X\"></sup> of the house of Jeroboam that led to its downfall and to its destruction<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9219Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9219Y\"></sup> from the face of the earth."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>At that time Abijah son of Jeroboam became ill,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and Jeroboam said to his wife, “Go, disguise yourself, so you won’t be recognized as the wife of Jeroboam. Then go to Shiloh. Ahijah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9221A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9221A\"></sup> the prophet is there—the one who told me I would be king over this people.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Take ten loaves of bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9222B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9222B\"></sup> with you, some cakes and a jar of honey, and go to him. He will tell you what will happen to the boy.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Jeroboam’s wife did what he said and went to Ahijah’s house in Shiloh.Now Ahijah could not see; his sight was gone because of his age.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had told Ahijah, “Jeroboam’s wife is coming to ask you about her son, for he is ill, and you are to give her such and such an answer. When she arrives, she will pretend to be someone else.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So when Ahijah heard the sound of her footsteps at the door, he said, “Come in, wife of Jeroboam. Why this pretense?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9225C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9225C\"></sup> I have been sent to you with bad news.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Go, tell Jeroboam that this is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, says:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9226D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9226D\"></sup> ‘I raised you up from among the people and appointed you ruler<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9226E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9226E\"></sup> over my people Israel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I tore<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9227F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9227F\"></sup> the kingdom away from the house of David and gave it to you, but you have not been like my servant David, who kept my commands and followed me with all his heart, doing only what was right<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9227G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9227G\"></sup> in my eyes.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You have done more evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9228H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9228H\"></sup> than all who lived before you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9228I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9228I\"></sup> You have made for yourself other gods, idols<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9228J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9228J\"></sup> made of metal; you have aroused<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9228K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9228K\"></sup> my anger and turned your back on me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9228L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9228L\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“‘Because of this, I am going to bring disaster<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9229M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9229M\"></sup> on the house of Jeroboam. I will cut off from Jeroboam every last male in Israel—slave or free.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9229N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9229N\"></sup> I will burn up the house of Jeroboam as one burns dung, until it is all gone.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9229O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9229O\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Dogs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9230P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9230P\"></sup> will eat those belonging to Jeroboam who die in the city, and the birds<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9230Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9230Q\"></sup> will feed on those who die in the country. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken!’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“As for you, go back home. When you set foot in your city, the boy will die.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>All Israel will mourn for him and bury him. He is the only one belonging to Jeroboam who will be buried, because he is the only one in the house of Jeroboam in whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, has found anything good.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9232R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9232R\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will raise up for himself a king over Israel who will cut off the family of Jeroboam. Even now this is beginning to happen.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will strike Israel, so that it will be like a reed swaying in the water. He will uproot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9234S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9234S\"></sup> Israel from this good land that he gave to their ancestors and scatter them beyond the Euphrates River, because they aroused<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9234T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9234T\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anger by making Asherah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9234U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9234U\"></sup> poles.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And he will give Israel up because of the sins<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9235V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9235V\"></sup> Jeroboam has committed and has caused Israel to commit.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Jeroboam’s wife got up and left and went to Tirzah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9236W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9236W\"></sup> As soon as she stepped over the threshold of the house, the boy died.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They buried him, and all Israel mourned for him, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said through his servant the prophet Ahijah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The other events of Jeroboam’s reign, his wars and how he ruled, are written in the book of the annals of the kings of Israel.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He reigned for twenty-two years and then rested with his ancestors. And Nadab his son succeeded him as king.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Rehoboam son of Solomon was king in Judah. He was forty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned seventeen years in Jerusalem, the city the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had chosen out of all the tribes of Israel in which to put his Name. His mother’s name was Naamah; she was an Ammonite.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9240Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9240Y\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9241Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9241Z\"></sup> did evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. By the sins they committed they stirred up his jealous anger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9241AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9241AA\"></sup> more than those who were before them had done.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>They also set up for themselves high places, sacred stones<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9242AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9242AB\"></sup> and Asherah poles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9242AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9242AC\"></sup> on every high hill and under every spreading tree.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9242AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9242AD\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>There were even male shrine prostitutes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9243AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9243AE\"></sup> in the land; the people engaged in all the detestable<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9243AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9243AF\"></sup> practices of the nations the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had driven out before the Israelites.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>In the fifth year of King Rehoboam, Shishak king of Egypt attacked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9244AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9244AG\"></sup> Jerusalem.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He carried off the treasures of the temple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9245AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9245AH\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the treasures of the royal palace. He took everything, including all the gold shields<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9245AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9245AI\"></sup> Solomon had made.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So King Rehoboam made bronze shields to replace them and assigned these to the commanders of the guard on duty at the entrance to the royal palace.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9246AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9246AJ\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Whenever the king went to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s temple, the guards bore the shields, and afterward they returned them to the guardroom.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>As for the other events of Rehoboam’s reign, and all he did, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Judah?",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>There was continual warfare<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9249AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9249AK\"></sup> between Rehoboam and Jeroboam.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And Rehoboam rested with his ancestors and was buried with them in the City of David. His mother’s name was Naamah; she was an Ammonite.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9250AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9250AL\"></sup> And Abijah his son succeeded him as king."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>In the eighteenth year of the reign of Jeroboam son of Nebat, Abijah became king of Judah,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and he reigned in Jerusalem three years. His mother’s name was Maakah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9252B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9252B\"></sup> daughter of Abishalom.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He committed all the sins his father had done before him; his heart was not fully devoted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9253C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9253C\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God, as the heart of David his forefather had been.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Nevertheless, for David’s sake the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God gave him a lamp<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9254D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9254D\"></sup> in Jerusalem by raising up a son to succeed him and by making Jerusalem strong.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For David had done what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and had not failed to keep<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9255E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9255E\"></sup> any of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s commands all the days of his life—except in the case of Uriah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9255F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9255F\"></sup> the Hittite.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>There was war<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9256G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9256G\"></sup> between Abijah and Jeroboam throughout Abijah’s lifetime.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>As for the other events of Abijah’s reign, and all he did, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Judah? There was war between Abijah and Jeroboam.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Abijah rested with his ancestors and was buried in the City of David. And Asa his son succeeded him as king.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>In the twentieth year of Jeroboam king of Israel, Asa became king of Judah,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and he reigned in Jerusalem forty-one years. His grandmother’s name was Maakah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9260J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9260J\"></sup> daughter of Abishalom.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Asa did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as his father David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9261K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9261K\"></sup> had done.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He expelled the male shrine prostitutes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9262L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9262L\"></sup> from the land and got rid of all the idols<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9262M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9262M\"></sup> his ancestors had made.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He even deposed his grandmother Maakah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9263N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9263N\"></sup> from her position as queen mother,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9263O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9263O\"></sup> because she had made a repulsive image for the worship of Asherah. Asa cut it down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9263P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9263P\"></sup> and burned it in the Kidron Valley.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Although he did not remove<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9264Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9264Q\"></sup> the high places, Asa’s heart was fully committed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9264R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9264R\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all his life.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He brought into the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the silver and gold and the articles that he and his father had dedicated.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9265S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9265S\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>There was war<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9266T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9266T\"></sup> between Asa and Baasha king of Israel throughout their reigns.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Baasha king of Israel went up against Judah and fortified Ramah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9267U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9267U\"></sup> to prevent anyone from leaving or entering the territory of Asa king of Judah.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Asa then took all the silver and gold that was left in the treasuries of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s temple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9268V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9268V\"></sup> and of his own palace. He entrusted it to his officials and sent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9268W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9268W\"></sup> them to Ben-Hadad<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9268X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9268X\"></sup> son of Tabrimmon, the son of Hezion, the king of Aram, who was ruling in Damascus.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Let there be a treaty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9269Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9269Y\"></sup> between me and you,” he said, “as there was between my father and your father. See, I am sending you a gift of silver and gold. Now break your treaty with Baasha king of Israel so he will withdraw from me.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Ben-Hadad agreed with King Asa and sent the commanders of his forces against the towns of Israel. He conquered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9270Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9270Z\"></sup> Ijon, Dan, Abel Beth Maakah and all Kinnereth in addition to Naphtali.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When Baasha heard this, he stopped building Ramah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9271AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9271AA\"></sup> and withdrew to Tirzah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9271AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9271AB\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then King Asa issued an order to all Judah—no one was exempt—and they carried away from Ramah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9272AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9272AC\"></sup> the stones and timber Baasha had been using there. With them King Asa<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9272AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9272AD\"></sup> built up Geba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9272AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9272AE\"></sup> in Benjamin, and also Mizpah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9272AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9272AF\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>As for all the other events of Asa’s reign, all his achievements, all he did and the cities he built, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Judah? In his old age, however, his feet became diseased.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then Asa rested with his ancestors and was buried with them in the city of his father David. And Jehoshaphat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9274AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9274AG\"></sup> his son succeeded him as king.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Nadab son of Jeroboam became king of Israel in the second year of Asa king of Judah, and he reigned over Israel two years.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9276AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9276AH\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, following the ways of his father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9276AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9276AI\"></sup> and committing the same sin his father had caused Israel to commit.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Baasha son of Ahijah from the tribe of Issachar plotted against him, and he struck him down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9277AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9277AJ\"></sup> at Gibbethon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9277AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9277AK\"></sup> a Philistine town, while Nadab and all Israel were besieging it.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Baasha killed Nadab in the third year of Asa king of Judah and succeeded him as king.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>As soon as he began to reign, he killed Jeroboam’s whole family.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9279AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9279AL\"></sup> He did not leave Jeroboam anyone that breathed, but destroyed them all, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> given through his servant Ahijah the Shilonite.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>This happened because of the sins<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9280AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9280AM\"></sup> Jeroboam had committed and had caused<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9280AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9280AN\"></sup> Israel to commit, and because he aroused the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>As for the other events of Nadab’s reign, and all he did, are they not written in the book of the annals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9281AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9281AO\"></sup> of the kings of Israel?",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>There was war<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9282AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9282AP\"></sup> between Asa and Baasha king of Israel throughout their reigns.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>In the third year of Asa king of Judah, Baasha son of Ahijah became king of all Israel in Tirzah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9283AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9283AQ\"></sup> and he reigned twenty-four years.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>He did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9284AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9284AR\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, following the ways of Jeroboam and committing the same sin Jeroboam had caused Israel to commit."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>Then the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Jehu<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9285A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9285A\"></sup> son of Hanani<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9285B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9285B\"></sup> concerning Baasha:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“I lifted you up from the dust<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9286C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9286C\"></sup> and appointed you ruler<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9286D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9286D\"></sup> over my people Israel, but you followed the ways of Jeroboam and caused<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9286E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9286E\"></sup> my people Israel to sin and to arouse my anger by their sins.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So I am about to wipe out Baasha<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9287F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9287F\"></sup> and his house,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9287G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9287G\"></sup> and I will make your house like that of Jeroboam son of Nebat.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Dogs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9288H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9288H\"></sup> will eat those belonging to Baasha who die in the city, and birds<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9288I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9288I\"></sup> will feed on those who die in the country.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>As for the other events of Baasha’s reign, what he did and his achievements, are they not written in the book of the annals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9289J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9289J\"></sup> of the kings of Israel?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Baasha rested with his ancestors and was buried in Tirzah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9290K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9290K\"></sup> And Elah his son succeeded him as king.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Moreover, the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9291L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9291L\"></sup> through the prophet Jehu<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9291M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9291M\"></sup> son of Hanani to Baasha and his house, because of all the evil he had done in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, arousing his anger by the things he did, becoming like the house of Jeroboam—and also because he destroyed it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>In the twenty-sixth year of Asa king of Judah, Elah son of Baasha became king of Israel, and he reigned in Tirzah two years.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Zimri, one of his officials, who had command of half his chariots, plotted against him. Elah was in Tirzah at the time, getting drunk<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9293N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9293N\"></sup> in the home of Arza, the palace administrator<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9293O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9293O\"></sup> at Tirzah.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Zimri came in, struck him down and killed him in the twenty-seventh year of Asa king of Judah. Then he succeeded him as king.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9294P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9294P\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>As soon as he began to reign and was seated on the throne, he killed off Baasha’s whole family.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9295Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9295Q\"></sup> He did not spare a single male, whether relative or friend.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So Zimri destroyed the whole family of Baasha, in accordance with the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoken against Baasha through the prophet Jehu—",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>because of all the sins Baasha and his son Elah had committed and had caused Israel to commit, so that they aroused the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, by their worthless idols.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9297R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9297R\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>As for the other events of Elah’s reign, and all he did, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Israel?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>In the twenty-seventh year of Asa king of Judah, Zimri reigned in Tirzah seven days. The army was encamped near Gibbethon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9299S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9299S\"></sup> a Philistine town.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When the Israelites in the camp heard that Zimri had plotted against the king and murdered him, they proclaimed Omri, the commander of the army, king over Israel that very day there in the camp.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Omri and all the Israelites with him withdrew from Gibbethon and laid siege to Tirzah.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When Zimri saw that the city was taken, he went into the citadel of the royal palace and set the palace on fire around him. So he died,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>because of the sins he had committed, doing evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and following the ways of Jeroboam and committing the same sin Jeroboam had caused Israel to commit.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As for the other events of Zimri’s reign, and the rebellion he carried out, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Israel?",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the people of Israel were split into two factions; half supported Tibni son of Ginath for king, and the other half supported Omri.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But Omri’s followers proved stronger than those of Tibni son of Ginath. So Tibni died and Omri became king.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>In the thirty-first year of Asa king of Judah, Omri became king of Israel, and he reigned twelve years, six of them in Tirzah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9307T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9307T\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He bought the hill of Samaria from Shemer for two talents of silver and built a city on the hill, calling it Samaria,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9308U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9308U\"></sup> after Shemer, the name of the former owner of the hill.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But Omri did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9309V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9309V\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and sinned more than all those before him.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He followed completely the ways of Jeroboam son of Nebat, committing the same sin Jeroboam had caused<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9310W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9310W\"></sup> Israel to commit, so that they aroused the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, by their worthless idols.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9310X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9310X\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>As for the other events of Omri’s reign, what he did and the things he achieved, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Israel?",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Omri rested with his ancestors and was buried in Samaria.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9312Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9312Y\"></sup> And Ahab his son succeeded him as king.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>In the thirty-eighth year of Asa king of Judah, Ahab son of Omri became king of Israel, and he reigned in Samaria over Israel twenty-two years.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Ahab son of Omri did more<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9314Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9314Z\"></sup> evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> than any of those before him.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>He not only considered it trivial to commit the sins of Jeroboam son of Nebat, but he also married<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9315AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9315AA\"></sup> Jezebel daughter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9315AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9315AB\"></sup> of Ethbaal king of the Sidonians, and began to serve Baal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9315AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9315AC\"></sup> and worship him.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>He set up an altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9316AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9316AD\"></sup> for Baal in the temple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9316AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9316AE\"></sup> of Baal that he built in Samaria.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Ahab also made an Asherah pole<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9317AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9317AF\"></sup> and did more<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9317AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9317AG\"></sup> to arouse the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, than did all the kings of Israel before him.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>In Ahab’s time, Hiel of Bethel rebuilt Jericho. He laid its foundations at the cost of his firstborn son Abiram, and he set up its gates at the cost of his youngest son Segub, in accordance with the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoken by Joshua son of Nun.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9318AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9318AH\"></sup>"
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>Now Elijah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9319A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9319A\"></sup> the Tishbite, from Tishbe in Gilead,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9319B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9319B\"></sup> said to Ahab, “As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, lives, whom I serve, there will be neither dew nor rain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9319C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9319C\"></sup> in the next few years except at my word.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Elijah:",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Leave here, turn eastward and hide<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9321D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9321D\"></sup> in the Kerith Ravine, east of the Jordan.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You will drink from the brook, and I have directed the ravens<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9322E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9322E\"></sup> to supply you with food there.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So he did what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had told him. He went to the Kerith Ravine, east of the Jordan, and stayed there.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The ravens brought him bread and meat in the morning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9324F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9324F\"></sup> and bread and meat in the evening, and he drank from the brook.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Some time later the brook dried up because there had been no rain in the land.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to him:",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Go at once to Zarephath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9327G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9327G\"></sup> in the region of Sidon and stay there. I have directed a widow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9327H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9327H\"></sup> there to supply you with food.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So he went to Zarephath. When he came to the town gate, a widow was there gathering sticks. He called to her and asked, “Would you bring me a little water in a jar so I may have a drink?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9328I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9328I\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>As she was going to get it, he called, “And bring me, please, a piece of bread.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God lives,” she replied, “I don’t have any bread—only a handful of flour in a jar and a little olive oil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9330J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9330J\"></sup> in a jug. I am gathering a few sticks to take home and make a meal for myself and my son, that we may eat it—and die.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Elijah said to her, “Don’t be afraid. Go home and do as you have said. But first make a small loaf of bread for me from what you have and bring it to me, and then make something for yourself and your son.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For this is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, says: ‘The jar of flour will not be used up and the jug of oil will not run dry until the day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sends rain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9332K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9332K\"></sup> on the land.’”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>She went away and did as Elijah had told her. So there was food every day for Elijah and for the woman and her family.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For the jar of flour was not used up and the jug of oil did not run dry, in keeping with the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoken by Elijah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Some time later the son of the woman who owned the house became ill. He grew worse and worse, and finally stopped breathing.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>She said to Elijah, “What do you have against me, man of God? Did you come to remind me of my sin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9336L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9336L\"></sup> and kill my son?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Give me your son,” Elijah replied. He took him from her arms, carried him to the upper room where he was staying, and laid him on his bed.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then he cried<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9338M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9338M\"></sup> out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, have you brought tragedy even on this widow I am staying with, by causing her son to die?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then he stretched<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9339N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9339N\"></sup> himself out on the boy three times and cried out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, let this boy’s life return to him!”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> heard Elijah’s cry, and the boy’s life returned to him, and he lived.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Elijah picked up the child and carried him down from the room into the house. He gave him to his mother<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9341O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9341O\"></sup> and said, “Look, your son is alive!”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then the woman said to Elijah, “Now I know<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9342P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9342P\"></sup> that you are a man of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9342Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9342Q\"></sup> and that the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from your mouth is the truth.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9342R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9342R\"></sup>"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>After a long time, in the third<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9343A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9343A\"></sup> year, the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Elijah: “Go and present<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9343B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9343B\"></sup> yourself to Ahab, and I will send rain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9343C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9343C\"></sup> on the land.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So Elijah went to present himself to Ahab.Now the famine was severe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9344D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9344D\"></sup> in Samaria,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and Ahab had summoned Obadiah, his palace administrator.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9345E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9345E\"></sup> (Obadiah was a devout believer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9345F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9345F\"></sup> in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>While Jezebel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9346G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9346G\"></sup> was killing off the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s prophets, Obadiah had taken a hundred prophets and hidden<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9346H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9346H\"></sup> them in two caves, fifty in each, and had supplied<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9346I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9346I\"></sup> them with food and water.)",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Ahab had said to Obadiah, “Go through the land to all the springs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9347J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9347J\"></sup> and valleys. Maybe we can find some grass to keep the horses and mules alive so we will not have to kill any of our animals.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9347K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9347K\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So they divided the land they were to cover, Ahab going in one direction and Obadiah in another.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>As Obadiah was walking along, Elijah met him. Obadiah recognized<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9349L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9349L\"></sup> him, bowed down to the ground, and said, “Is it really you, my lord Elijah?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Yes,” he replied. “Go tell your master, ‘Elijah is here.’”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“What have I done wrong,” asked Obadiah, “that you are handing your servant over to Ahab to be put to death?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God lives, there is not a nation or kingdom where my master has not sent someone to look<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9352M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9352M\"></sup> for you. And whenever a nation or kingdom claimed you were not there, he made them swear they could not find you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But now you tell me to go to my master and say, ‘Elijah is here.’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I don’t know where the Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9354N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9354N\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> may carry you when I leave you. If I go and tell Ahab and he doesn’t find you, he will kill me. Yet I your servant have worshiped the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> since my youth.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Haven’t you heard, my lord, what I did while Jezebel was killing the prophets of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>? I hid a hundred of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s prophets in two caves, fifty in each, and supplied them with food and water.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And now you tell me to go to my master and say, ‘Elijah is here.’ He will kill me!”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Elijah said, “As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Almighty lives, whom I serve, I will surely present<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9357O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9357O\"></sup> myself to Ahab today.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So Obadiah went to meet Ahab and told him, and Ahab went to meet Elijah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When he saw Elijah, he said to him, “Is that you, you troubler<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9359P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9359P\"></sup> of Israel?”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“I have not made trouble for Israel,” Elijah replied. “But you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9360Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9360Q\"></sup> and your father’s family have. You have abandoned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9360R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9360R\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s commands and have followed the Baals.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now summon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9361S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9361S\"></sup> the people from all over Israel to meet me on Mount Carmel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9361T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9361T\"></sup> And bring the four hundred and fifty prophets of Baal and the four hundred prophets of Asherah, who eat at Jezebel’s table.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9361U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9361U\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Ahab sent word throughout all Israel and assembled the prophets on Mount Carmel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9362V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9362V\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Elijah went before the people and said, “How long will you waver<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9363W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9363W\"></sup> between two opinions? If the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9363X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9363X\"></sup> is God, follow him; but if Baal is God, follow him.”But the people said nothing.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Elijah said to them, “I am the only one of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s prophets left,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9364Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9364Y\"></sup> but Baal has four hundred and fifty prophets.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9364Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9364Z\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Get two bulls for us. Let Baal’s prophets choose one for themselves, and let them cut it into pieces and put it on the wood but not set fire to it. I will prepare the other bull and put it on the wood but not set fire to it.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then you call<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9366AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9366AA\"></sup> on the name of your god, and I will call on the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9366AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9366AB\"></sup> The god who answers by fire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9366AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9366AC\"></sup>—he is God.”Then all the people said, “What you say is good.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Elijah said to the prophets of Baal, “Choose one of the bulls and prepare it first, since there are so many of you. Call on the name of your god, but do not light the fire.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So they took the bull given them and prepared it.Then they called<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9368AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9368AD\"></sup> on the name of Baal from morning till noon. “Baal, answer us!” they shouted. But there was no response;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9368AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9368AE\"></sup> no one answered. And they danced around the altar they had made.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>At noon Elijah began to taunt them. “Shout louder!” he said. “Surely he is a god! Perhaps he is deep in thought, or busy, or traveling. Maybe he is sleeping and must be awakened.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9369AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9369AF\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So they shouted louder and slashed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9370AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9370AG\"></sup> themselves with swords and spears, as was their custom, until their blood flowed.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Midday passed, and they continued their frantic prophesying until the time for the evening sacrifice.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9371AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9371AH\"></sup> But there was no response, no one answered, no one paid attention.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9371AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9371AI\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Elijah said to all the people, “Come here to me.” They came to him, and he repaired the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9372AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9372AJ\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which had been torn down.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Elijah took twelve stones, one for each of the tribes descended from Jacob, to whom the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had come, saying, “Your name shall be Israel.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9373AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9373AK\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>With the stones he built an altar in the name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9374AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9374AL\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he dug a trench around it large enough to hold two seahs of seed.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He arranged<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9375AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9375AM\"></sup> the wood, cut the bull into pieces and laid it on the wood. Then he said to them, “Fill four large jars with water and pour it on the offering and on the wood.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“Do it again,” he said, and they did it again.“Do it a third time,” he ordered, and they did it the third time.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The water ran down around the altar and even filled the trench.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>At the time<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9378AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9378AN\"></sup> of sacrifice, the prophet Elijah stepped forward and prayed: “<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Abraham,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9378AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9378AO\"></sup> Isaac and Israel, let it be known<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9378AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9378AP\"></sup> today that you are God in Israel and that I am your servant and have done all these things at your command.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9378AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9378AQ\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Answer me, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, answer me, so these people will know<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9379AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9379AR\"></sup> that you, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, are God, and that you are turning their hearts back again.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Then the fire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9380AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9380AS\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> fell and burned up the sacrifice, the wood, the stones and the soil, and also licked up the water in the trench.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>When all the people saw this, they fell prostrate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9381AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9381AT\"></sup> and cried, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—he is God! The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—he is God!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9381AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9381AU\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Then Elijah commanded them, “Seize the prophets of Baal. Don’t let anyone get away!” They seized them, and Elijah had them brought down to the Kishon Valley<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9382AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9382AV\"></sup> and slaughtered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9382AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9382AW\"></sup> there.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And Elijah said to Ahab, “Go, eat and drink, for there is the sound of a heavy rain.”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>So Ahab went off to eat and drink, but Elijah climbed to the top of Carmel, bent down to the ground and put his face between his knees.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9384AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9384AX\"></sup>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>“Go and look toward the sea,” he told his servant. And he went up and looked.“There is nothing there,” he said.Seven times Elijah said, “Go back.”",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>The seventh time<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9386AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9386AY\"></sup> the servant reported, “A cloud<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9386AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9386AZ\"></sup> as small as a man’s hand is rising from the sea.”So Elijah said, “Go and tell Ahab, ‘Hitch up your chariot and go down before the rain stops you.’”",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Meanwhile, the sky grew black with clouds, the wind rose, a heavy rain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9387BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9387BA\"></sup> started falling and Ahab rode off to Jezreel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9387BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9387BB\"></sup>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>The power<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9388BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9388BC\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came on Elijah and, tucking his cloak into his belt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9388BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9388BD\"></sup> he ran ahead of Ahab all the way to Jezreel."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>Now Ahab told Jezebel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9389A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9389A\"></sup> everything Elijah had done and how he had killed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9389B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9389B\"></sup> all the prophets with the sword.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So Jezebel sent a messenger to Elijah to say, “May the gods deal with me, be it ever so severely,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9390C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9390C\"></sup> if by this time tomorrow I do not make your life like that of one of them.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9390D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9390D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Elijah was afraid and ran<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9391E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9391E\"></sup> for his life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9391F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9391F\"></sup> When he came to Beersheba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9391G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9391G\"></sup> in Judah, he left his servant there,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>while he himself went a day’s journey into the wilderness. He came to a broom bush,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9392H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9392H\"></sup> sat down under it and prayed that he might die. “I have had enough, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,” he said. “Take my life;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9392I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9392I\"></sup> I am no better than my ancestors.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then he lay down under the bush and fell asleep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9393J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9393J\"></sup>All at once an angel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9393K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9393K\"></sup> touched him and said, “Get up and eat.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He looked around, and there by his head was some bread baked over hot coals, and a jar of water. He ate and drank and then lay down again.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came back a second time and touched him and said, “Get up and eat, for the journey is too much for you.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So he got up and ate and drank. Strengthened by that food, he traveled forty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9396L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9396L\"></sup> days and forty nights until he reached Horeb,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9396M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9396M\"></sup> the mountain of God.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>There he went into a cave<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9397N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9397N\"></sup> and spent the night.And the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to him: “What are you doing here, Elijah?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9397O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9397O\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He replied, “I have been very zealous<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9398P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9398P\"></sup> for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God Almighty. The Israelites have rejected your covenant,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9398Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9398Q\"></sup> torn down your altars,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9398R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9398R\"></sup> and put your prophets to death with the sword. I am the only one left,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9398S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9398S\"></sup> and now they are trying to kill me too.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “Go out and stand on the mountain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9399T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9399T\"></sup> in the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is about to pass by.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9399U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9399U\"></sup>Then a great and powerful wind<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9399V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9399V\"></sup> tore the mountains apart and shattered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9399W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9399W\"></sup> the rocks before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was not in the wind. After the wind there was an earthquake, but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was not in the earthquake.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>After the earthquake came a fire,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9400X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9400X\"></sup> but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was not in the fire. And after the fire came a gentle whisper.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9400Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9400Y\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When Elijah heard it, he pulled his cloak over his face<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9401Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9401Z\"></sup> and went out and stood at the mouth of the cave.Then a voice said to him, “What are you doing here, Elijah?”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He replied, “I have been very zealous for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God Almighty. The Israelites have rejected your covenant, torn down your altars, and put your prophets to death with the sword. I am the only one left,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9402AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9402AA\"></sup> and now they are trying to kill me too.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Go back the way you came, and go to the Desert of Damascus. When you get there, anoint Hazael<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9403AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9403AB\"></sup> king over Aram.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Also, anoint<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9404AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9404AC\"></sup> Jehu son of Nimshi king over Israel, and anoint Elisha<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9404AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9404AD\"></sup> son of Shaphat from Abel Meholah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9404AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9404AE\"></sup> to succeed you as prophet.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Jehu will put to death any who escape the sword of Hazael,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9405AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9405AF\"></sup> and Elisha will put to death any who escape the sword of Jehu.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9405AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9405AG\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Yet I reserve<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9406AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9406AH\"></sup> seven thousand in Israel—all whose knees have not bowed down to Baal and whose mouths have not kissed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9406AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9406AI\"></sup> him.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So Elijah went from there and found Elisha son of Shaphat. He was plowing with twelve yoke of oxen, and he himself was driving the twelfth pair. Elijah went up to him and threw his cloak<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9407AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9407AJ\"></sup> around him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Elisha then left his oxen and ran after Elijah. “Let me kiss my father and mother goodbye,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9408AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9408AK\"></sup> he said, “and then I will come with you.”“Go back,” Elijah replied. “What have I done to you?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So Elisha left him and went back. He took his yoke of oxen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9409AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9409AL\"></sup> and slaughtered them. He burned the plowing equipment to cook the meat and gave it to the people, and they ate. Then he set out to follow Elijah and became his servant.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9409AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9409AM\"></sup>"
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>Now Ben-Hadad<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9410A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9410A\"></sup> king of Aram mustered his entire army. Accompanied by thirty-two kings with their horses and chariots, he went up and besieged Samaria<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9410B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9410B\"></sup> and attacked it.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He sent messengers into the city to Ahab king of Israel, saying, “This is what Ben-Hadad says:",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>‘Your silver and gold are mine, and the best of your wives and children are mine.’”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The king of Israel answered, “Just as you say, my lord the king. I and all I have are yours.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The messengers came again and said, “This is what Ben-Hadad says: ‘I sent to demand your silver and gold, your wives and your children.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But about this time tomorrow I am going to send my officials to search your palace and the houses of your officials. They will seize everything you value and carry it away.’”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The king of Israel summoned all the elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9416C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9416C\"></sup> of the land and said to them, “See how this man is looking for trouble!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9416D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9416D\"></sup> When he sent for my wives and my children, my silver and my gold, I did not refuse him.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The elders and the people all answered, “Don’t listen to him or agree to his demands.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So he replied to Ben-Hadad’s messengers, “Tell my lord the king, ‘Your servant will do all you demanded the first time, but this demand I cannot meet.’” They left and took the answer back to Ben-Hadad.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Ben-Hadad sent another message to Ahab: “May the gods deal with me, be it ever so severely, if enough dust<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9419E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9419E\"></sup> remains in Samaria to give each of my men a handful.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The king of Israel answered, “Tell him: ‘One who puts on his armor should not boast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9420F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9420F\"></sup> like one who takes it off.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Ben-Hadad heard this message while he and the kings were drinking<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9421G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9421G\"></sup> in their tents, and he ordered his men: “Prepare to attack.” So they prepared to attack the city.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Meanwhile a prophet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9422H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9422H\"></sup> came to Ahab king of Israel and announced, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: ‘Do you see this vast army? I will give it into your hand today, and then you will know<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9422I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9422I\"></sup> that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“But who will do this?” asked Ahab.The prophet replied, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: ‘The junior officers under the provincial commanders will do it.’”“And who will start<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9423J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9423J\"></sup> the battle?” he asked.The prophet answered, “You will.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So Ahab summoned the 232 junior officers under the provincial commanders. Then he assembled the rest of the Israelites, 7,000 in all.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>They set out at noon while Ben-Hadad and the 32 kings allied with him were in their tents getting drunk.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9425K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9425K\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The junior officers under the provincial commanders went out first.Now Ben-Hadad had dispatched scouts, who reported, “Men are advancing from Samaria.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He said, “If they have come out for peace, take them alive; if they have come out for war, take them alive.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The junior officers under the provincial commanders marched out of the city with the army behind them",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and each one struck down his opponent. At that, the Arameans fled, with the Israelites in pursuit. But Ben-Hadad king of Aram escaped on horseback with some of his horsemen.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The king of Israel advanced and overpowered the horses and chariots and inflicted heavy losses on the Arameans.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Afterward, the prophet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9431L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9431L\"></sup> came to the king of Israel and said, “Strengthen your position and see what must be done, because next spring<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9431M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9431M\"></sup> the king of Aram will attack you again.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Meanwhile, the officials of the king of Aram advised him, “Their gods are gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9432N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9432N\"></sup> of the hills. That is why they were too strong for us. But if we fight them on the plains, surely we will be stronger than they.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Do this: Remove all the kings from their commands and replace them with other officers.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>You must also raise an army like the one you lost—horse for horse and chariot for chariot—so we can fight Israel on the plains. Then surely we will be stronger than they.” He agreed with them and acted accordingly.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The next spring<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9435O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9435O\"></sup> Ben-Hadad mustered the Arameans and went up to Aphek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9435P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9435P\"></sup> to fight against Israel.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When the Israelites were also mustered and given provisions, they marched out to meet them. The Israelites camped opposite them like two small flocks of goats, while the Arameans covered the countryside.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9436Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9436Q\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The man of God came up and told the king of Israel, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: ‘Because the Arameans think the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is a god of the hills and not a god<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9437R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9437R\"></sup> of the valleys, I will deliver this vast army into your hands, and you will know<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9437S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9437S\"></sup> that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>For seven days they camped opposite each other, and on the seventh day the battle was joined. The Israelites inflicted a hundred thousand casualties on the Aramean foot soldiers in one day.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The rest of them escaped to the city of Aphek,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9439T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9439T\"></sup> where the wall collapsed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9439U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9439U\"></sup> on twenty-seven thousand of them. And Ben-Hadad fled to the city and hid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9439V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9439V\"></sup> in an inner room.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>His officials said to him, “Look, we have heard that the kings of Israel are merciful.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9440W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9440W\"></sup> Let us go to the king of Israel with sackcloth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9440X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9440X\"></sup> around our waists and ropes around our heads. Perhaps he will spare your life.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Wearing sackcloth around their waists and ropes around their heads, they went to the king of Israel and said, “Your servant Ben-Hadad says: ‘Please let me live.’”The king answered, “Is he still alive? He is my brother.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The men took this as a good sign and were quick to pick up his word. “Yes, your brother Ben-Hadad!” they said.“Go and get him,” the king said. When Ben-Hadad came out, Ahab had him come up into his chariot.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“I will return the cities<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9443Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9443Y\"></sup> my father took from your father,” Ben-Hadad<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9443Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9443Z\"></sup> offered. “You may set up your own market areas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9443AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9443AA\"></sup> in Damascus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9443AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9443AB\"></sup> as my father did in Samaria.”Ahab said, “On the basis of a treaty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9443AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9443AC\"></sup> I will set you free.” So he made a treaty with him, and let him go.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>By the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> one of the company of the prophets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9444AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9444AD\"></sup> said to his companion, “Strike me with your weapon,” but he refused.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9444AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9444AE\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>So the prophet said, “Because you have not obeyed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as soon as you leave me a lion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9445AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9445AF\"></sup> will kill you.” And after the man went away, a lion found him and killed him.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>The prophet found another man and said, “Strike me, please.” So the man struck him and wounded him.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Then the prophet went and stood by the road waiting for the king. He disguised himself with his headband down over his eyes.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>As the king passed by, the prophet called out to him, “Your servant went into the thick of the battle, and someone came to me with a captive and said, ‘Guard this man. If he is missing, it will be your life for his life,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9448AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9448AG\"></sup> or you must pay a talent of silver.’",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>While your servant was busy here and there, the man disappeared.”“That is your sentence,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9449AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9449AH\"></sup> the king of Israel said. “You have pronounced it yourself.”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Then the prophet quickly removed the headband from his eyes, and the king of Israel recognized him as one of the prophets.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>He said to the king, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: ‘You<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9451AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9451AI\"></sup> have set free a man I had determined should die.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9451AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9451AJ\"></sup> Therefore it is your life for his life,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9451AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9451AK\"></sup> your people for his people.’”",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Sullen and angry,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9452AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9452AL\"></sup> the king of Israel went to his palace in Samaria."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>Some time later there was an incident involving a vineyard belonging to Naboth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9453A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9453A\"></sup> the Jezreelite. The vineyard was in Jezreel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9453B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9453B\"></sup> close to the palace of Ahab king of Samaria.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Ahab said to Naboth, “Let me have your vineyard to use for a vegetable garden, since it is close to my palace. In exchange I will give you a better vineyard or, if you prefer, I will pay you whatever it is worth.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But Naboth replied, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> forbid that I should give you the inheritance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9455C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9455C\"></sup> of my ancestors.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Ahab went home, sullen and angry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9456D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9456D\"></sup> because Naboth the Jezreelite had said, “I will not give you the inheritance of my ancestors.” He lay on his bed sulking and refused<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9456E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9456E\"></sup> to eat.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>His wife Jezebel came in and asked him, “Why are you so sullen? Why won’t you eat?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He answered her, “Because I said to Naboth the Jezreelite, ‘Sell me your vineyard; or if you prefer, I will give you another vineyard in its place.’ But he said, ‘I will not give you my vineyard.’”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Jezebel his wife said, “Is this how you act as king over Israel? Get up and eat! Cheer up. I’ll get you the vineyard<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9459F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9459F\"></sup> of Naboth the Jezreelite.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So she wrote letters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9460G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9460G\"></sup> in Ahab’s name, placed his seal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9460H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9460H\"></sup> on them, and sent them to the elders and nobles who lived in Naboth’s city with him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>In those letters she wrote:“Proclaim a day of fasting and seat Naboth in a prominent place among the people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But seat two scoundrels<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9462I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9462I\"></sup> opposite him and have them bring charges that he has cursed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9462J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9462J\"></sup> both God and the king. Then take him out and stone him to death.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So the elders and nobles who lived in Naboth’s city did as Jezebel directed in the letters she had written to them.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They proclaimed a fast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9464K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9464K\"></sup> and seated Naboth in a prominent place among the people.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then two scoundrels came and sat opposite him and brought charges against Naboth before the people, saying, “Naboth has cursed both God and the king.” So they took him outside the city and stoned him to death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9465L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9465L\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then they sent word to Jezebel: “Naboth has been stoned to death.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>As soon as Jezebel heard that Naboth had been stoned to death, she said to Ahab, “Get up and take possession of the vineyard<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9467M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9467M\"></sup> of Naboth the Jezreelite that he refused to sell you. He is no longer alive, but dead.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When Ahab heard that Naboth was dead, he got up and went down to take possession of Naboth’s vineyard.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Elijah the Tishbite:",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Go down to meet Ahab king of Israel, who rules in Samaria. He is now in Naboth’s vineyard, where he has gone to take possession of it.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Say to him, ‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: Have you not murdered a man and seized his property?’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9471N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9471N\"></sup> Then say to him, ‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: In the place where dogs licked up Naboth’s blood,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9471O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9471O\"></sup> dogs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9471P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9471P\"></sup> will lick up your blood—yes, yours!’”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Ahab said to Elijah, “So you have found me, my enemy!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9472Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9472Q\"></sup>“I have found you,” he answered, “because you have sold<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9472R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9472R\"></sup> yourself to do evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He says, ‘I am going to bring disaster on you. I will wipe out your descendants and cut off from Ahab every last male<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9473S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9473S\"></sup> in Israel—slave or free.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9473T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9473T\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>I will make your house<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9474U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9474U\"></sup> like that of Jeroboam son of Nebat and that of Baasha son of Ahijah, because you have aroused my anger and have caused Israel to sin.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9474V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9474V\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“And also concerning Jezebel the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: ‘Dogs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9475W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9475W\"></sup> will devour Jezebel by the wall of Jezreel.’",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Dogs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9476X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9476X\"></sup> will eat those belonging to Ahab who die in the city, and the birds<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9476Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9476Y\"></sup> will feed on those who die in the country.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>(There was never<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9477Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9477Z\"></sup> anyone like Ahab, who sold himself to do evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, urged on by Jezebel his wife.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He behaved in the vilest manner by going after idols, like the Amorites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9478AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9478AA\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> drove out before Israel.)",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When Ahab heard these words, he tore his clothes, put on sackcloth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9479AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9479AB\"></sup> and fasted. He lay in sackcloth and went around meekly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9479AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9479AC\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Elijah the Tishbite:",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“Have you noticed how Ahab has humbled himself before me? Because he has humbled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9481AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9481AD\"></sup> himself, I will not bring this disaster in his day,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9481AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9481AE\"></sup> but I will bring it on his house in the days of his son.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9481AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9481AF\"></sup>"
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>For three years there was no war between Aram and Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But in the third year Jehoshaphat king of Judah went down to see the king of Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The king of Israel had said to his officials, “Don’t you know that Ramoth Gilead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9484B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9484B\"></sup> belongs to us and yet we are doing nothing to retake it from the king of Aram?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So he asked Jehoshaphat, “Will you go with me to fight<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9485C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9485C\"></sup> against Ramoth Gilead?”Jehoshaphat replied to the king of Israel, “I am as you are, my people as your people, my horses as your horses.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But Jehoshaphat also said to the king of Israel, “First seek the counsel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9486D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9486D\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So the king of Israel brought together the prophets—about four hundred men—and asked them, “Shall I go to war against Ramoth Gilead, or shall I refrain?”“Go,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9487E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9487E\"></sup> they answered, “for the Lord will give it into the king’s hand.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9487F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9487F\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But Jehoshaphat asked, “Is there no longer a prophet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9488G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9488G\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> here whom we can inquire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9488H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9488H\"></sup> of?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The king of Israel answered Jehoshaphat, “There is still one prophet through whom we can inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but I hate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9489I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9489I\"></sup> him because he never prophesies anything good<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9489J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9489J\"></sup> about me, but always bad. He is Micaiah son of Imlah.”“The king should not say such a thing,” Jehoshaphat replied.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So the king of Israel called one of his officials and said, “Bring Micaiah son of Imlah at once.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Dressed in their royal robes, the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat king of Judah were sitting on their thrones at the threshing floor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9491K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9491K\"></sup> by the entrance of the gate of Samaria, with all the prophets prophesying before them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now Zedekiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9492L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9492L\"></sup> son of Kenaanah had made iron horns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9492M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9492M\"></sup> and he declared, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: ‘With these you will gore the Arameans until they are destroyed.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>All the other prophets were prophesying the same thing. “Attack Ramoth Gilead and be victorious,” they said, “for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will give it into the king’s hand.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The messenger who had gone to summon Micaiah said to him, “Look, the other prophets without exception are predicting success for the king. Let your word agree with theirs, and speak favorably.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9494N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9494N\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But Micaiah said, “As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, I can tell him only what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> tells me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9495O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9495O\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When he arrived, the king asked him, “Micaiah, shall we go to war against Ramoth Gilead, or not?”“Attack and be victorious,” he answered, “for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will give it into the king’s hand.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The king said to him, “How many times must I make you swear to tell me nothing but the truth in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Micaiah answered, “I saw all Israel scattered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9498P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9498P\"></sup> on the hills like sheep without a shepherd,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9498Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9498Q\"></sup> and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, ‘These people have no master. Let each one go home in peace.’”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “Didn’t I tell you that he never prophesies anything good about me, but only bad?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Micaiah continued, “Therefore hear the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: I saw the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sitting on his throne<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9500R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9500R\"></sup> with all the multitudes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9500S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9500S\"></sup> of heaven standing around him on his right and on his left.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, ‘Who will entice Ahab into attacking Ramoth Gilead and going to his death there?’“One suggested this, and another that.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Finally, a spirit came forward, stood before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, ‘I will entice him.’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“‘By what means?’ the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> asked.“‘I will go out and be a deceiving<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9503T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9503T\"></sup> spirit in the mouths of all his prophets,’ he said.“‘You will succeed in enticing him,’ said the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. ‘Go and do it.’",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“So now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has put a deceiving<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9504U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9504U\"></sup> spirit in the mouths of all these prophets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9504V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9504V\"></sup> of yours. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has decreed disaster<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9504W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9504W\"></sup> for you.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then Zedekiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9505X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9505X\"></sup> son of Kenaanah went up and slapped<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9505Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9505Y\"></sup> Micaiah in the face. “Which way did the spirit from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> go when he went from me to speak<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9505Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9505Z\"></sup> to you?” he asked.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Micaiah replied, “You will find out on the day you go to hide<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9506AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9506AA\"></sup> in an inner room.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The king of Israel then ordered, “Take Micaiah and send him back to Amon the ruler of the city and to Joash the king’s son",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and say, ‘This is what the king says: Put this fellow in prison<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9508AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9508AB\"></sup> and give him nothing but bread and water until I return safely.’”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Micaiah declared, “If you ever return safely, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not spoken<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9509AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9509AC\"></sup> through me.” Then he added, “Mark my words, all you people!”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat king of Judah went up to Ramoth Gilead.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “I will enter the battle in disguise,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9511AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9511AE\"></sup> but you wear your royal robes.” So the king of Israel disguised himself and went into battle.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Now the king of Aram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9512AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9512AF\"></sup> had ordered his thirty-two chariot commanders, “Do not fight with anyone, small or great, except the king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9512AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9512AG\"></sup> of Israel.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>When the chariot commanders saw Jehoshaphat, they thought, “Surely this is the king of Israel.” So they turned to attack him, but when Jehoshaphat cried out,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>the chariot commanders saw that he was not the king of Israel and stopped pursuing him.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But someone drew his bow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9515AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9515AH\"></sup> at random and hit the king of Israel between the sections of his armor. The king told his chariot driver, “Wheel around and get me out of the fighting. I’ve been wounded.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>All day long the battle raged, and the king was propped up in his chariot facing the Arameans. The blood from his wound ran onto the floor of the chariot, and that evening he died.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>As the sun was setting, a cry spread through the army: “Every man to his town. Every man to his land!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9517AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9517AI\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>So the king died and was brought to Samaria, and they buried him there.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>They washed the chariot at a pool in Samaria (where the prostitutes bathed), and the dogs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9519AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9519AJ\"></sup> licked up his blood, as the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had declared.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>As for the other events of Ahab’s reign, including all he did, the palace he built and adorned with ivory,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9520AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9520AK\"></sup> and the cities he fortified, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Israel?",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Ahab rested with his ancestors. And Ahaziah his son succeeded him as king.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Jehoshaphat son of Asa became king of Judah in the fourth year of Ahab king of Israel.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Jehoshaphat was thirty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem twenty-five years. His mother’s name was Azubah daughter of Shilhi.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>In everything he followed the ways of his father Asa<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9524AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9524AM\"></sup> and did not stray from them; he did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. The high places,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9524AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9524AN\"></sup> however, were not removed, and the people continued to offer sacrifices and burn incense there.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Jehoshaphat was also at peace with the king of Israel.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>As for the other events of Jehoshaphat’s reign, the things he achieved and his military exploits, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Judah?",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>He rid the land of the rest of the male shrine prostitutes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9527AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9527AO\"></sup> who remained there even after the reign of his father Asa.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>There was then no king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9528AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9528AP\"></sup> in Edom; a provincial governor ruled.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Now Jehoshaphat built a fleet of trading ships<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9529AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9529AQ\"></sup> to go to Ophir for gold, but they never set sail—they were wrecked at Ezion Geber.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9529AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9529AR\"></sup>",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>At that time Ahaziah son of Ahab said to Jehoshaphat, “Let my men sail with yours,” but Jehoshaphat refused.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Then Jehoshaphat rested with his ancestors and was buried with them in the city of David his father. And Jehoram his son succeeded him as king.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Ahaziah son of Ahab became king of Israel in Samaria in the seventeenth year of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, and he reigned over Israel two years.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>He did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9533AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9533AS\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, because he followed the ways of his father and mother and of Jeroboam son of Nebat, who caused Israel to sin.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>He served and worshiped Baal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9534AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9534AT\"></sup> and aroused the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, just as his father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9534AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9534AU\"></sup> had done."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;